WEBVTT

1
00:00:08.425 --> 00:00:09.884
[woman 1 speaks indistinctly]

2
00:00:11.000 --> 00:00:17.074
Do you want subtitles for any video?
-=[ ai.OpenSubtitles.com ]=-

3
00:00:32.824 --> 00:00:35.326
[woman 1 speaks indistinctly]

4
00:00:39.247 --> 00:00:41.291
[mysterious. ethereal music plays]

5
00:00:41.374 --> 00:00:43.710
[woman 1] <i>New Boston. 911.</i>
<i>What's your emergency?</i>

6
00:00:43.793 --> 00:00:46.921
[Taylor Parker] <i>I need an ambulance</i>
<i>'cause I started having my baby.</i>

7
00:00:47.005 --> 00:00:49.174
[woman 1] <i>Stay on the line.</i>
<i>I'm gonna get you to LifeNet.</i>

8
00:00:49.257 --> 00:00:51.551
-[Taylor] <i>I have a trooper behind me.</i>
-<i>Stay on the line.</i>

9
00:00:51.634 --> 00:00:53.303
<i>It's gonna be okay. Stay on the line.</i>

10
00:00:53.386 --> 00:00:54.971
-[dial tone pulses]
-[siren wails]

11
00:00:55.055 --> 00:00:57.140
[phone dialing]

12
00:00:57.223 --> 00:00:58.349
[man] <i>Emergency.</i>

13
00:00:58.433 --> 00:01:02.187
[Taylor sobs] <i>I just need</i>
<i>an ambulance to get to Idabel.</i>

14
00:01:02.270 --> 00:01:05.482
[woman 1] <i>She's gone into labor.</i>
<i>She has a state trooper behind her.</i>

15
00:01:06.357 --> 00:01:07.358
[man] <i>Okay.</i>

16
00:01:07.442 --> 00:01:09.652
-[Taylor] <i>Hurry! Please!</i>
-[man] <i>Is the trooper with her?</i>

17
00:01:09.736 --> 00:01:13.031
[woman 1] <i>Yeah. he was. uh.</i>
<i>pulling her over as she called.</i>

18
00:01:14.407 --> 00:01:15.950
[man] <i>Ma'am. are you still here with me?</i>

19
00:01:16.034 --> 00:01:18.244
-[trooper] What's wrong. ma'am?
-I had my baby.

20
00:01:18.328 --> 00:01:21.081
And I'm trying to get to I-Idabel Hospital
where my husband--

21
00:01:21.164 --> 00:01:24.292
-[trooper] Idabel?
-Yeah. my husband's up there.

22
00:01:24.375 --> 00:01:26.795
[trooper] Need LifeNet out.
uh. to my location.

23
00:01:26.878 --> 00:01:29.923
Lady in this vehicle
who appeared to just have a baby.

24
00:01:30.006 --> 00:01:33.259
She was carrying the baby in her lap.
Umbilical cord is still attached.

25
00:01:33.927 --> 00:01:35.804
She's not breathing.

26
00:01:37.013 --> 00:01:39.974
[trooper] The baby's not breathing.
She's doing CPR on the baby right now.

27
00:01:40.058 --> 00:01:43.144
Can you just put me in your car
and drive us so we're not sitting?

28
00:01:43.228 --> 00:01:44.521
Please. I'm begging you.

29
00:01:44.604 --> 00:01:47.148
[trooper] There's nothing I can do.
You're gonna need EMS.

30
00:01:47.232 --> 00:01:50.860
I'm fine. if you'll just get us there
as quick as possible.

31
00:01:50.944 --> 00:01:53.321
[trooper] Thank you.
Uh. LifeNet's already on scene.

32
00:01:53.404 --> 00:01:56.116
-[medic 1] You just gave birth?
-[medic 2] Turn around and sit down.

33
00:01:56.199 --> 00:01:57.408
[Taylor] Okay.

34
00:01:57.492 --> 00:01:59.077
[medic 1] How old you say you was?

35
00:01:59.160 --> 00:02:00.703
-[Taylor] 27.
-[medic 1] 27?

36
00:02:00.787 --> 00:02:03.456
-[Taylor] I think I was born in '92.
-[medic 1] Okay.

37
00:02:04.791 --> 00:02:07.877
So you was-- You was on your way
to Idabel to-- to have the baby?

38
00:02:07.961 --> 00:02:09.504
-[woman] Yeah.
-[medic 1] Okay.

39
00:02:09.587 --> 00:02:11.339
-[people chatter]
-[medic 1] Okay.

40
00:02:11.422 --> 00:02:13.216
-[Taylor sobs]
-[medic 1] Just relax. darling.

41
00:02:13.299 --> 00:02:15.218
[siren wails]

42
00:02:19.806 --> 00:02:22.183
[cop 1 whispers] Do not let her
out that door.

43
00:02:25.311 --> 00:02:28.523
-I'm gonna need--
-Getting real. real jumpy in there.

44
00:02:29.149 --> 00:02:31.067
[cop 1] So she shows no signs…

45
00:02:31.151 --> 00:02:33.862
You won't-- You can't check
for hemorrhaging?

46
00:02:34.737 --> 00:02:36.906
She should be hemorrhaging by now.

47
00:02:37.574 --> 00:02:38.616
She's in there.

48
00:02:38.700 --> 00:02:43.621
She refuses to have a vaginal check
to make sure she's not hemorrhaging.

49
00:02:43.705 --> 00:02:46.249
They've done ultrasound and HCG.

50
00:02:46.332 --> 00:02:48.209
and it doesn't show
that she's been pregnant.

51
00:02:48.293 --> 00:02:49.586
They have the placenta.

52
00:02:49.669 --> 00:02:51.796
-Where is she?
-[cop 1] She is in the room.

53
00:02:51.880 --> 00:02:53.423
-You're not letting her leave?
-No.

54
00:02:54.132 --> 00:02:56.092
-[masked nurse] Can I help you?
-[cop 1] This is…

55
00:02:56.176 --> 00:02:57.844
-This is a big deal.
-[cop 1] Yeah.

56
00:02:57.927 --> 00:02:59.554
[masked nurse] Okay. yes. Are you ready?

57
00:02:59.637 --> 00:03:01.764
[eerie music plays]

58
00:03:01.848 --> 00:03:02.974
[man] Hey. there.

59
00:03:03.933 --> 00:03:04.976
What's your name?

60
00:03:05.059 --> 00:03:06.227
Taylor Parker.

61
00:03:06.311 --> 00:03:08.938
Taylor. Hey.
My name is Chad Dansby. I'm a…

62
00:03:09.731 --> 00:03:13.234
I'm an OSBI agent up here.
and I heard you brought your baby in.

63
00:03:13.318 --> 00:03:14.402
Yes. sir.

64
00:03:17.405 --> 00:03:19.699
Did you give birth
on the side of the road or something?

65
00:03:19.782 --> 00:03:21.784
-Yes. sir.
-Oh. okay.

66
00:03:22.368 --> 00:03:25.038
Where was that? Here? In McCurtain County?

67
00:03:25.121 --> 00:03:27.540
No. it was in De Kalb.

68
00:03:27.624 --> 00:03:29.167
De Kalb. Down in Texas?

69
00:03:29.250 --> 00:03:30.543
-Yes. sir.
-Oh. okay.

70
00:03:30.627 --> 00:03:34.255
[voice breaking] Did I do something wrong
for them bringing me over here?

71
00:03:34.756 --> 00:03:37.217
So you-- you gave birth to this child?

72
00:03:38.635 --> 00:03:39.761
Yes. I--

73
00:03:40.511 --> 00:03:42.847
[cop 1] We're--
We're just making sure. okay?

74
00:03:43.765 --> 00:03:47.268
If there's anything you need
to talk to us about. you can.

75
00:03:48.311 --> 00:03:51.231
I don't know what everybody
wants me to talk about.

76
00:03:51.814 --> 00:03:54.067
I'm just trying to figure out
where this baby came from.

77
00:03:55.693 --> 00:03:58.488
I just told y'all what happened.

78
00:03:58.571 --> 00:03:59.489
Okay.

79
00:04:00.156 --> 00:04:03.201
What's the doctor gonna find
when he comes in and checks you?

80
00:04:03.284 --> 00:04:05.203
Is he gonna find you just gave birth?

81
00:04:06.746 --> 00:04:07.914
-I--
-They can tell.

82
00:04:07.997 --> 00:04:09.832
When he looks. he can tell
in about a second

83
00:04:09.916 --> 00:04:11.501
if you gave birth or not.

84
00:04:11.584 --> 00:04:13.336
O-- Okay.

85
00:04:14.295 --> 00:04:15.213
Yeah.

86
00:04:16.881 --> 00:04:19.384
So is he gonna find
that you gave birth this morning?

87
00:04:20.343 --> 00:04:22.428
-Yes.
-Okay.

88
00:04:23.012 --> 00:04:25.556
-Let's see.
-[Chad] So we'll jump out.

89
00:04:25.640 --> 00:04:26.933
[doctor] Sit you up.

90
00:04:27.016 --> 00:04:29.143
All right. well. let me have
them sit you up there

91
00:04:29.227 --> 00:04:31.062
where I can see what I'm doing.

92
00:04:32.730 --> 00:04:34.732
I didn't-- It doesn't look
like she had a baby.

93
00:04:34.816 --> 00:04:35.858
-[cop 1] It doesn't?
-No.

94
00:04:35.942 --> 00:04:36.901
[cop 1] Okay.

95
00:04:36.985 --> 00:04:39.779
Does not look
like she had a baby down there.

96
00:04:39.862 --> 00:04:40.697
[cop 2] Get ready.

97
00:04:40.780 --> 00:04:42.407
[Chad] Where'd this baby come from?

98
00:04:42.949 --> 00:04:45.076
It's mine!

99
00:04:45.159 --> 00:04:46.244
Can't be.

100
00:04:46.995 --> 00:04:47.996
Can't be.

101
00:04:48.997 --> 00:04:50.999
[eerie music continues playing]

102
00:05:06.597 --> 00:05:07.974
[music turns ethereal]

103
00:05:35.293 --> 00:05:37.128
[insects chirping]

104
00:05:40.423 --> 00:05:41.674
[birds chirp]

105
00:05:41.758 --> 00:05:43.760
[sprawling. forlorn music plays]

106
00:05:51.684 --> 00:05:54.729
[woman] Coming from a small town.
you can trust easy.

107
00:05:54.812 --> 00:05:56.606
And. um…

108
00:05:57.607 --> 00:06:01.944
And I guess that's
kind of the direction it went.

109
00:06:03.446 --> 00:06:05.239
[man 1] From my perspective.

110
00:06:05.323 --> 00:06:08.076
{\an8}there's way more good people
than there are bad.

111
00:06:08.951 --> 00:06:10.995
But there's evil in our land.

112
00:06:11.871 --> 00:06:14.290
Evil people do evil things.

113
00:06:16.667 --> 00:06:19.045
[man 2] Come on. come on. come on.

114
00:06:19.128 --> 00:06:23.591
[man 1] There is an inner spirit
that tries to protect us.

115
00:06:24.967 --> 00:06:27.428
A really. really subtle voice.

116
00:06:27.512 --> 00:06:30.515
And we don't have enough sense
to listen to it sometimes.

117
00:06:30.598 --> 00:06:31.891
Most of the time. actually.

118
00:06:34.352 --> 00:06:37.939
[woman 2] It's still very raw
to all of us.

119
00:06:38.606 --> 00:06:41.609
We still are just kind of like.
"I can't believe this happened."

120
00:06:41.692 --> 00:06:45.029
Like. "Why didn't we listen
to the people that told us?"

121
00:06:45.696 --> 00:06:48.324
{\an8}"I still can't believe it."

122
00:06:53.663 --> 00:06:55.331
[interviewer] Who is Taylor?

123
00:06:56.958 --> 00:06:59.293
Taylor is…

124
00:07:02.839 --> 00:07:04.215
hard to describe.

125
00:07:04.298 --> 00:07:05.508
[tense music plays]

126
00:07:05.591 --> 00:07:08.261
I think that it's hard to describe Taylor

127
00:07:08.344 --> 00:07:14.684
because there's so many aspects to her
and all her personalities.

128
00:07:15.685 --> 00:07:20.481
The Taylor that I knew was.
at one time. a good friend.

129
00:07:20.565 --> 00:07:23.985
She made you feel
like the best person on the planet.

130
00:07:24.902 --> 00:07:26.612
She came off as a normal country girl.

131
00:07:26.696 --> 00:07:29.198
She came off as a--
She was fresh from the country.

132
00:07:29.282 --> 00:07:30.491
I mean. like a country hick.

133
00:07:30.575 --> 00:07:34.537
And with her looks. a lot of people
would kind of flirt with her about it.

134
00:07:35.037 --> 00:07:38.291
She loved attention. Loves attention.

135
00:07:38.374 --> 00:07:39.292
[chimes]

136
00:07:39.375 --> 00:07:41.711
Her whole mission in life

137
00:07:41.794 --> 00:07:44.589
was to be the pretty girl
that caught the eye of a guy.

138
00:07:44.672 --> 00:07:47.508
{\an8}And then she met Wade.

139
00:07:56.559 --> 00:07:59.145
Is it hot in here to y'all.
or is it just me?

140
00:07:59.228 --> 00:08:01.606
[interviewer] It's--
It's mostly you. probably.

141
00:08:01.689 --> 00:08:03.649
{\an8}[chuckles]

142
00:08:03.733 --> 00:08:06.694
{\an8}[announcer] <i>…two. three.</i>
<i>let's cut 'em loose!</i>

143
00:08:06.777 --> 00:08:09.238
[gentle folk music plays]

144
00:08:09.322 --> 00:08:12.116
[Wade] It all kind of started
in the summer of 2019.

145
00:08:12.200 --> 00:08:15.369
[announcer] <i>Make some noise.</i>
<i>encourage 'em. Come on!</i>

146
00:08:15.453 --> 00:08:17.413
[Wade] I remember
that time that I met Taylor.

147
00:08:18.664 --> 00:08:22.126
She'd seen me at the rodeo
and then wanted to know if I was single

148
00:08:22.210 --> 00:08:23.878
and wanted to hang out sometime.

149
00:08:24.462 --> 00:08:26.005
She was a pretty girl. you know.

150
00:08:26.088 --> 00:08:29.175
just kind of lit up the room
when she walked in.

151
00:08:29.258 --> 00:08:30.927
smiling from ear to ear.

152
00:08:31.010 --> 00:08:34.597
I was like. well. it wouldn't hurt nothing
to go out to eat or something with her

153
00:08:34.680 --> 00:08:36.557
and. you know. see
what kind of person she is.

154
00:08:36.641 --> 00:08:39.101
And it just kind of went from there.

155
00:08:39.644 --> 00:08:43.898
{\an8}She comes to work.
and she is just. I mean. just smitten

156
00:08:43.981 --> 00:08:46.859
{\an8}and tickled pink. and was talking
about how much she likes this guy.

157
00:08:46.943 --> 00:08:50.571
He was just a good old country boy
that was laid back.

158
00:08:50.655 --> 00:08:52.073
He was a hard worker.

159
00:08:52.156 --> 00:08:55.076
He seemed just. you know. a good catch
that had never been married.

160
00:08:55.159 --> 00:08:56.827
no past baggage.

161
00:08:57.620 --> 00:09:00.122
[Connie] She just kind of came
out of nowhere. you know?

162
00:09:00.206 --> 00:09:02.750
{\an8}But she was pretty crazy about him.

163
00:09:02.833 --> 00:09:05.336
{\an8}and it was important to her
to make him happy.

164
00:09:05.419 --> 00:09:09.298
And I could see why Wade
would be attracted to her.

165
00:09:09.382 --> 00:09:11.050
[Taylor laughs]

166
00:09:11.133 --> 00:09:12.677
Damn it. Wade!

167
00:09:12.760 --> 00:09:16.347
[mock gasps] I'm making a video
of you being abusive! [laughs]

168
00:09:17.223 --> 00:09:20.601
[Wade] You know. most girls.
they don't really like the country life.

169
00:09:20.685 --> 00:09:23.020
but she was different
about that kind of stuff.

170
00:09:24.480 --> 00:09:29.068
She'd been around the horses. cows.
all the farm stuff. driving tractor.

171
00:09:30.027 --> 00:09:32.280
I was a country guy.
She was a country girl.

172
00:09:33.698 --> 00:09:35.366
That's what she was attracted to.

173
00:09:37.118 --> 00:09:38.995
[Wade] Oh. man! Oh. he let it go!

174
00:09:39.078 --> 00:09:40.788
-Get it. Frank!
-[dogs bark]

175
00:09:41.581 --> 00:09:43.583
[Roger] Seemed like they were
doing things together.

176
00:09:43.666 --> 00:09:46.460
{\an8}She'd go hog hunting with him.
She'd help him catch hogs.

177
00:09:48.254 --> 00:09:51.007
[Connie] She was right there.
shoulder to shoulder.

178
00:09:51.090 --> 00:09:54.844
He seemed like he was happy.
and people liked her.

179
00:09:55.344 --> 00:09:56.971
{\an8}Man. I thought she was fantastic.

180
00:09:57.054 --> 00:10:00.391
She was somebody that you'd want
to hang around with.

181
00:10:00.474 --> 00:10:02.143
you know. you could kick it off with.

182
00:10:02.226 --> 00:10:03.603
[snaps] Quick like. you know?

183
00:10:03.686 --> 00:10:06.397
[Stephanie] She actually came
right up to me and gave me a hug.

184
00:10:06.480 --> 00:10:10.151
{\an8}She was so glad to meet me.
She loved our family.

185
00:10:10.735 --> 00:10:12.528
[Codey] My wife loved her. you know?

186
00:10:12.612 --> 00:10:15.114
"Wade. you done found--"
You know? "A good one right here."

187
00:10:15.197 --> 00:10:16.907
"This one. you need to marry her."

188
00:10:22.496 --> 00:10:27.335
[Angela] Wade was working with my husband.
and they were right around the corner.

189
00:10:27.418 --> 00:10:31.172
{\an8}A lot of times. weekly.
we would have-- have 'em come over.

190
00:10:31.255 --> 00:10:32.882
and we'd grill steaks out.

191
00:10:33.466 --> 00:10:37.887
When I first met Taylor.
she was working for a hiring agency.

192
00:10:38.512 --> 00:10:41.974
But she told me her family
had lots of money.

193
00:10:42.058 --> 00:10:46.437
I was told she had
a-- a grandma and grandpa

194
00:10:47.104 --> 00:10:49.357
that lived down at-- around Bassett.

195
00:10:49.440 --> 00:10:51.567
[droning folk music plays]

196
00:10:51.651 --> 00:10:53.903
They're the one that holds all the money

197
00:10:53.986 --> 00:10:56.238
of all the oil wells
in the Sulphur River Bottoms.

198
00:10:57.239 --> 00:10:58.991
I mean. it was a lot of money.

199
00:10:59.867 --> 00:11:03.788
I was like. "Gosh. Wade. if she's got all
this kind of money and stuff. you know?"

200
00:11:03.871 --> 00:11:07.500
"And. man. she's got a good personality.
you know. she likes to hang out."

201
00:11:07.583 --> 00:11:09.710
"That's what you've always
been looking for." You know?

202
00:11:10.461 --> 00:11:13.214
[Wade] I knew they had some money.
but I didn't know how much.

203
00:11:13.297 --> 00:11:18.177
She just said she has plenty set aside
that the grandma done worked out with her.

204
00:11:18.260 --> 00:11:21.597
[Angela] Then she told me that her mother
was fighting with her about money.

205
00:11:21.681 --> 00:11:24.517
that money she wasn't actually getting.

206
00:11:24.600 --> 00:11:28.437
but someday she was gonna be
this millionaire.

207
00:11:28.521 --> 00:11:30.106
I mean. that's what she told us.

208
00:11:30.189 --> 00:11:34.860
Her mother was going to get her
cut completely out of all the money.

209
00:11:34.944 --> 00:11:36.404
She wasn't gonna get nothing.

210
00:11:36.487 --> 00:11:39.073
She hated her mother.
and her mother hated her.

211
00:11:39.156 --> 00:11:43.411
Taylor just portrayed her mom just to be
a-- pretty much. a greedy monster. Um…

212
00:11:43.494 --> 00:11:45.037
[music turns lively]

213
00:11:45.121 --> 00:11:47.748
I was just kind of there
being as supportive as I could.

214
00:11:47.832 --> 00:11:51.627
but it was just-- it was never-ending
of the family drama.

215
00:11:52.503 --> 00:11:56.215
From my perspective.
they didn't actually fit.

216
00:11:56.298 --> 00:11:58.926
He was born to a family of workers.

217
00:11:59.009 --> 00:12:00.970
and he wasn't making
any money to speak of.

218
00:12:01.053 --> 00:12:06.308
and she was born in a family
of people that had lots of money.

219
00:12:06.392 --> 00:12:08.894
From my experiences of life.

220
00:12:08.978 --> 00:12:13.107
I've never really seen a relationship
like that work for very long.

221
00:12:17.570 --> 00:12:20.406
[dogs barking]

222
00:12:35.921 --> 00:12:38.132
[Connie] All of a sudden.
she sold all of her furniture

223
00:12:38.215 --> 00:12:41.677
and pretty much emptied the house out
that she was renting.

224
00:12:41.761 --> 00:12:43.345
and she moved in with him.

225
00:12:43.429 --> 00:12:46.849
And I think that that was
kind of the point where I realized

226
00:12:46.932 --> 00:12:50.478
it was… becoming more serious.

227
00:12:50.561 --> 00:12:52.563
[tender music plays]

228
00:12:54.356 --> 00:12:59.487
[Connie] It was kind of strange that she
didn't seem to have a lot to store.

229
00:12:59.570 --> 00:13:02.698
Just kind of traveled light. you know?

230
00:13:04.366 --> 00:13:07.536
[Wade] She told me that because her mom
don't want her having no inheritance

231
00:13:07.620 --> 00:13:09.622
and no property and no money.

232
00:13:09.705 --> 00:13:13.959
and she don't know what extreme
her mom's gonna go to.

233
00:13:14.043 --> 00:13:16.378
She said. "I think it's a good idea
if I move in with you

234
00:13:16.462 --> 00:13:17.797
for more protection."

235
00:13:18.380 --> 00:13:19.840
And so she did.

236
00:13:19.924 --> 00:13:22.134
[music turns intriguing]

237
00:13:22.218 --> 00:13:23.677
She had two kids.

238
00:13:23.761 --> 00:13:25.721
Her daughter would be with us
during the week.

239
00:13:25.805 --> 00:13:29.475
but we never seen the boy that often.

240
00:13:30.768 --> 00:13:34.647
I noticed instead of really spending
one-on-one time with her.

241
00:13:35.397 --> 00:13:38.400
it was more "What was Wade doing?"
You know?

242
00:13:38.484 --> 00:13:41.278
[laughing] We're trying
to figure out how to do your trailer.

243
00:13:41.862 --> 00:13:44.448
This is broke. Wade.
You're missing a bolt.

244
00:13:44.532 --> 00:13:47.117
I can fix that so don't-- don't be mad.

245
00:13:47.201 --> 00:13:48.911
[Stephanie] She did seem
to have a big heart.

246
00:13:48.994 --> 00:13:51.247
Would do anything in the world for Wade.

247
00:13:51.330 --> 00:13:52.373
Anything he asked.

248
00:13:52.456 --> 00:13:54.875
She would mow the yard.
she would have supper ready.

249
00:13:54.959 --> 00:13:56.168
I think he loved that.

250
00:13:56.836 --> 00:13:59.088
[Wade] She'd make sure
she had a good meal cooked

251
00:13:59.171 --> 00:14:01.173
when I got home from work.

252
00:14:01.257 --> 00:14:03.008
She would take care of the animals.

253
00:14:03.092 --> 00:14:07.930
Anything I asked her to do. she would do.
So she did pull her weight.

254
00:14:12.560 --> 00:14:18.566
After she started living with Wade.
she was over at my house. uh. constantly.

255
00:14:18.649 --> 00:14:20.109
So by this time. you know.

256
00:14:20.192 --> 00:14:24.405
I've heard story upon story upon story
of-- you know. about her mother.

257
00:14:24.488 --> 00:14:28.701
Then one day she told me
her mother had lost favor

258
00:14:28.784 --> 00:14:32.913
with the rest of her family
because of her threats to Taylor.

259
00:14:32.997 --> 00:14:36.584
So she suddenly was gonna get
more money from her grandmother.

260
00:14:37.376 --> 00:14:40.087
[Connie] She was going
to inherit eight million or so.

261
00:14:40.170 --> 00:14:41.005
[bold music plays]

262
00:14:41.088 --> 00:14:45.175
Eight million dollars was just something
that you don't hear every day.

263
00:14:45.801 --> 00:14:47.720
[Wade] I didn't really know what to think.

264
00:14:47.803 --> 00:14:52.182
but she said that'll make things
a lot-- a lot better off now.

265
00:14:52.266 --> 00:14:55.686
[Codey] He was thinking her grandparents
were gonna give all that to her

266
00:14:55.769 --> 00:14:56.937
in the will and stuff.

267
00:14:57.021 --> 00:15:01.233
and then Wade was like. "Gosh. damn.
if they do that. then damn. I'm set."

268
00:15:01.317 --> 00:15:04.278
[bold music intensifies]

269
00:15:07.114 --> 00:15:10.618
[Angela] When all of a sudden this seemed
like they were gonna get all this money.

270
00:15:10.701 --> 00:15:13.162
I mean. they were buying everything.
They were buying cars

271
00:15:13.245 --> 00:15:15.998
and side-by-sides and cattle.

272
00:15:16.874 --> 00:15:18.667
They done bought a $20.000 side-by-side.

273
00:15:18.751 --> 00:15:21.879
done bought him
a $60.000. $80.000 tractor.

274
00:15:21.962 --> 00:15:24.548
and now done went
and bought a $87.000 truck.

275
00:15:24.632 --> 00:15:27.092
I mean. money's got to be coming
from somewhere. you know.

276
00:15:27.176 --> 00:15:29.136
[Roger] It was like a Cadillac. you know.

277
00:15:29.219 --> 00:15:32.014
So I'm sitting here.
thinking. "That's a $100.000 truck."

278
00:15:32.097 --> 00:15:34.266
"There's no way
you can afford that pickup."

279
00:15:34.350 --> 00:15:35.893
He said. "Well. I'll tell you.

280
00:15:36.518 --> 00:15:38.938
there's some things
you don't know about me."

281
00:15:40.105 --> 00:15:42.316
I'd been shopping for a car
for quite a while.

282
00:15:42.399 --> 00:15:45.110
and she pulled up in my driveway.

283
00:15:45.194 --> 00:15:47.988
and she said.
"How do you like my new car?"

284
00:15:48.697 --> 00:15:51.033
And I said. "Man. that's nice." you know?

285
00:15:51.116 --> 00:15:54.745
And she said. "Well. it's yours.
I bought you a car."

286
00:15:54.828 --> 00:15:57.164
Posted it on Facebook.

287
00:15:57.247 --> 00:16:01.710
You can tell from the picture
that I was kind of reeling from it all.

288
00:16:03.212 --> 00:16:07.883
You know. with Wade. I really saw
a side of him that I hadn't seen before.

289
00:16:07.967 --> 00:16:10.719
Like. he deserved more.

290
00:16:10.803 --> 00:16:14.056
But the big thing was this big ranch
that Wade had wanted.

291
00:16:14.139 --> 00:16:17.059
and she was gonna make sure he got that.

292
00:16:18.018 --> 00:16:22.231
[Wade] She was telling me she would like
to buy a nice piece of property somewhere.

293
00:16:22.314 --> 00:16:24.483
It didn't really matter the price.

294
00:16:24.566 --> 00:16:29.863
{\an8}So I told her. I said. "Well. there's
this property in Harris. Oklahoma."

295
00:16:29.947 --> 00:16:32.074
"It's right there on Red River."

296
00:16:32.157 --> 00:16:34.326
-[mouse clicking]
-[suspenseful music continues]

297
00:16:39.456 --> 00:16:40.833
[clock ticking]

298
00:16:46.797 --> 00:16:52.469
{\an8}Fall of '19. I received a phone call
from a woman named Taylor.

299
00:16:53.220 --> 00:16:56.849
She was a very well
put-together young lady.

300
00:16:56.932 --> 00:16:58.976
spoke in a very professional manner.

301
00:16:59.059 --> 00:17:03.147
who expressed an interest in a property
that's. uh. known as Pecan Point.

302
00:17:04.189 --> 00:17:06.191
-[cows low]
-[keyboard clacking]

303
00:17:07.234 --> 00:17:09.903
Her and Wade obviously had spoken
about it at length.

304
00:17:09.987 --> 00:17:12.364
and they were looking for
what they referred to

305
00:17:12.448 --> 00:17:15.200
as "a local sportsman's paradise."

306
00:17:15.868 --> 00:17:20.622
Wade was very interested
in the local feral hog population.

307
00:17:21.457 --> 00:17:23.792
[woman] She had on jeans.
she was well-dressed.

308
00:17:23.876 --> 00:17:26.211
Her hair was nicely done.

309
00:17:26.295 --> 00:17:29.298
{\an8}But you know. especially in the farm
and ranch industry.

310
00:17:29.381 --> 00:17:32.301
{\an8}uh. those are very grounded people

311
00:17:32.384 --> 00:17:37.848
who might not look as though they could
purchase a multimillion-dollar property.

312
00:17:37.931 --> 00:17:43.896
but. in fact. they could purchase
multiple million-dollar properties.

313
00:17:44.730 --> 00:17:48.859
[Rusty] My initial impression was
that she probably had some family money.

314
00:17:48.942 --> 00:17:53.739
She certainly indicated that.
and was ready to make an offer.

315
00:17:53.822 --> 00:17:56.325
Four million dollars. I believe.

316
00:17:56.408 --> 00:17:59.661
She was adamant that we're--
she was gonna pay cash.

317
00:18:00.829 --> 00:18:02.122
We were rooting for her.

318
00:18:04.291 --> 00:18:07.461
[man] I seen that. and he said.
"You'll be surprised at what that means."

319
00:18:07.544 --> 00:18:09.922
It's got the house.
and all the barns. and that part--

320
00:18:10.005 --> 00:18:11.799
It's got one big barn on it.

321
00:18:11.882 --> 00:18:16.512
and then it has. I guess.
it's kinda like a makeshift half-house.

322
00:18:16.595 --> 00:18:19.056
and then their pecan cleaning production.

323
00:18:19.139 --> 00:18:22.017
but we don't get
any of the equipment on that.

324
00:18:22.101 --> 00:18:26.271
[Connie] When we went to my sister's
for the family gathering that day.

325
00:18:26.355 --> 00:18:31.151
they decided to have a little presentation
in front of everybody.

326
00:18:31.235 --> 00:18:34.196
It was a big deal for Taylor and Wade.

327
00:18:34.279 --> 00:18:36.490
so we filmed it.

328
00:18:36.573 --> 00:18:41.120
…we're gonna run the pecans on it.
We have about 500 acres.

329
00:18:41.203 --> 00:18:46.208
[Connie] Wade kind of took a back seat.
and she stood in the middle of the room.

330
00:18:46.291 --> 00:18:49.086
and all the attention was on her.

331
00:18:49.169 --> 00:18:53.340
We're pretty excited.
It's a big adventure for both of us.

332
00:18:54.383 --> 00:18:56.260
[Connie] Everybody's listening.

333
00:18:56.343 --> 00:18:59.304
and they're all just
kind of in awe of it all.

334
00:18:59.388 --> 00:19:00.764
Kinda cool.

335
00:19:00.848 --> 00:19:02.057
Wow.

336
00:19:03.183 --> 00:19:05.602
-That's a super cool place.
-[man] Well. Merry Christmas.

337
00:19:05.686 --> 00:19:06.770
[woman 1 laughs]

338
00:19:06.854 --> 00:19:09.773
-[Wade] Thank you. man.
-[woman 2] Merry Christmas.

339
00:19:10.524 --> 00:19:12.025
It's "Pecan Bend" now.

340
00:19:12.109 --> 00:19:13.861
[Wade] She just. she shined.

341
00:19:14.611 --> 00:19:18.657
I mean. she just kind of painted a--
a pretty picture. kind of for the future.

342
00:19:18.740 --> 00:19:20.492
[Connie] The thing about it was.

343
00:19:20.576 --> 00:19:24.663
Pecan Point wasn't something
she would necessarily want herself.

344
00:19:24.746 --> 00:19:26.748
but she knew Wade would.

345
00:19:26.832 --> 00:19:28.083
["Carol of the Bells" plays]

346
00:19:28.167 --> 00:19:31.712
[Wade] She made it all look and seem.
like. you know. pretty normal

347
00:19:31.795 --> 00:19:34.464
or. you know. a dream come true.

348
00:19:34.548 --> 00:19:35.924
more or less.

349
00:19:36.008 --> 00:19:37.342
[tense. ethereal music plays]

350
00:19:37.426 --> 00:19:40.637
You know. I hadn't known Taylor
but just a couple months.

351
00:19:40.721 --> 00:19:44.016
and something just kind of still
questioned me about. you know.

352
00:19:44.099 --> 00:19:46.852
"This is all happening way too fast."

353
00:19:47.686 --> 00:19:51.648
[interviewer] What happened
to the car that she gave you?

354
00:19:51.732 --> 00:19:54.234
[Connie] I had it about three weeks.
and she said.

355
00:19:54.318 --> 00:19:58.488
"I need y'all to bring the car
to Wade's and park it in the driveway."

356
00:19:58.572 --> 00:20:02.409
"Patterson Nissan.
they're coming to pick it up on a recall."

357
00:20:02.492 --> 00:20:06.455
So I finally called the dealership.
and I said. "What's going on with my car?"

358
00:20:07.039 --> 00:20:09.249
They said.
"Ma'am. that car wasn't paid for."

359
00:20:09.333 --> 00:20:11.335
"That's why we came and got it."

360
00:20:11.835 --> 00:20:13.629
It was repossessed.

361
00:20:14.504 --> 00:20:15.797
I said. "Oh."

362
00:20:17.090 --> 00:20:19.092
"Okay." [chuckles]

363
00:20:20.469 --> 00:20:23.180
You know. a mom just knows. They know.

364
00:20:23.263 --> 00:20:26.850
You just know when it's your kid.
It's a sixth sense or something.

365
00:20:26.934 --> 00:20:29.478
You just know
that something's just not right.

366
00:20:30.729 --> 00:20:32.147
I just began to worry.

367
00:20:32.231 --> 00:20:35.359
you know. "What's gonna happen
if this doesn't go through?"

368
00:20:35.442 --> 00:20:38.612
Because I knew
he couldn't afford those things.

369
00:20:38.695 --> 00:20:40.030
He couldn't pay for that.

370
00:20:42.824 --> 00:20:44.826
[Rusty] Her and Wade signed the offer.

371
00:20:46.245 --> 00:20:47.996
In the next couple of days.

372
00:20:48.080 --> 00:20:52.960
we got it back.
and I asked her to verify funds.

373
00:20:53.543 --> 00:20:56.672
[Renee] She was finally going
to be able to get her inheritance.

374
00:20:56.755 --> 00:21:00.008
We have to do a little bit more vetting.
if you will.

375
00:21:00.092 --> 00:21:05.597
when it's a cash transaction
coming from a trust or an inheritance.

376
00:21:05.681 --> 00:21:06.682
[telephone rings]

377
00:21:06.765 --> 00:21:09.518
[Rusty] I might get a call
from her lawyer.

378
00:21:09.601 --> 00:21:13.272
I've received a couple of letters
from a local banker.

379
00:21:13.355 --> 00:21:18.527
Many times these forms of communication
would come to us at odd hours.

380
00:21:18.610 --> 00:21:21.154
shortly after five o'clock
in the afternoon

381
00:21:21.238 --> 00:21:24.032
or maybe on a Saturday morning.

382
00:21:24.116 --> 00:21:30.372
Taylor put me in contact with Shelly Linx.
who oversaw her oil lease money.

383
00:21:30.455 --> 00:21:31.623
[second telephone rings]

384
00:21:31.707 --> 00:21:36.878
I had. uh. made
a couple attempts to reach Shelly.

385
00:21:36.962 --> 00:21:40.590
We would call. We would leave a voicemail.

386
00:21:40.674 --> 00:21:44.511
One time. Shelly emailed us back.
kind of reprimanding us

387
00:21:44.594 --> 00:21:47.597
for asking too many personal questions
about her customer.

388
00:21:47.681 --> 00:21:48.682
[woman] "Mr. Lowe…"

389
00:21:48.765 --> 00:21:51.476
[woman and Rusty] "Bank information
is completely confidential."

390
00:21:51.560 --> 00:21:55.105
"The clients are not okay
with the seller calling their bank

391
00:21:55.188 --> 00:21:58.483
and are firm on their decision
in that matter."

392
00:21:58.567 --> 00:22:00.527
"Thank you. Shelly."

393
00:22:00.610 --> 00:22:03.488
I-- I mean. I was getting
my butt chewed out. obviously.

394
00:22:03.572 --> 00:22:05.240
for checking up on her.

395
00:22:08.118 --> 00:22:12.164
As time moved on.
Taylor referred us to an uncle

396
00:22:12.247 --> 00:22:14.374
that was from the Northwest named Butch.

397
00:22:15.334 --> 00:22:19.838
And Uncle Butch was going
to wire transfer $300.000

398
00:22:19.921 --> 00:22:25.927
so she could write two checks
for $150.000 each as escrow money.

399
00:22:26.011 --> 00:22:29.181
And… that didn't happen either.

400
00:22:31.516 --> 00:22:33.518
[dog barks in distance]

401
00:22:35.187 --> 00:22:37.314
[Wade whistling softly to dogs]

402
00:22:43.070 --> 00:22:44.696
[Wade] I didn't really know what to think.

403
00:22:45.447 --> 00:22:48.492
I've never dealt with this much
at one time. this fast.

404
00:22:48.575 --> 00:22:50.369
[hogs grunting]

405
00:22:51.578 --> 00:22:54.164
I think there's something else going on.

406
00:22:55.874 --> 00:23:00.003
A lot of times I would go to work
and confide with my boss. Roger.

407
00:23:00.087 --> 00:23:02.172
He'd say.
"Everything happens for a reason."

408
00:23:02.255 --> 00:23:05.759
He said. you know. "Me and my wife
both love her to death."

409
00:23:05.842 --> 00:23:08.637
"I don't see her
taking you down no bad path."

410
00:23:08.720 --> 00:23:12.307
"So whatever. you know. she's telling you.
it's gonna-- it's gonna be the truth."

411
00:23:12.391 --> 00:23:13.475
[dreary music plays]

412
00:23:13.558 --> 00:23:16.269
All of a sudden the money wasn't coming
like it's supposed to.

413
00:23:16.353 --> 00:23:18.647
and there's more and more fights.

414
00:23:18.730 --> 00:23:19.773
[phone chimes]

415
00:23:22.984 --> 00:23:26.113
[Stephanie] She would text me
and say. "I don't think he loves me."

416
00:23:26.196 --> 00:23:27.447
"I bought him this truck.

417
00:23:27.531 --> 00:23:29.908
and he's not acting
any different towards me."

418
00:23:29.991 --> 00:23:32.619
"I think he may be talking
to somebody else."

419
00:23:33.203 --> 00:23:35.205
[Taylor] <i>Can you please call me back?</i>

420
00:23:35.288 --> 00:23:37.791
[urgently] <i>I have tried</i>
<i>and tried to call you.</i>

421
00:23:38.375 --> 00:23:41.253
<i>I am trying to figure something out</i>
<i>so I can tell Shelly.</i>

422
00:23:41.336 --> 00:23:44.840
<i>I need you to call me back on--</i>
<i>someway. somehow.</i>

423
00:23:46.091 --> 00:23:49.010
[Angela] She was. uh. stressful
all the time

424
00:23:49.094 --> 00:23:50.887
that she was gonna lose Wade.

425
00:23:54.891 --> 00:23:58.478
[woman] I work from home. and I could see
his house from where I was working.

426
00:23:58.562 --> 00:24:01.898
{\an8}And Wade would be riding
the side-by-side out to the farm.

427
00:24:01.982 --> 00:24:04.734
{\an8}and she was just holding him.

428
00:24:04.818 --> 00:24:09.322
embracing him
like. just. "This is my guy."

429
00:24:09.406 --> 00:24:10.949
Like. "I love him so much."

430
00:24:11.032 --> 00:24:15.996
And Wade would just be…
He just seemed very distant from her.

431
00:24:24.754 --> 00:24:29.718
[Angela] She came over to my house one day
when her and Wade were fighting a lot.

432
00:24:31.178 --> 00:24:35.182
She wanted to see me
as a chiropractor. which I am.

433
00:24:35.765 --> 00:24:38.852
She came in.
she was just real ecstatic. real happy.

434
00:24:39.811 --> 00:24:46.234
She said. "I want you to talk to my body
and ask if I'm pregnant."

435
00:24:46.318 --> 00:24:49.321
I asked her. I said.
"Why do you think you're pregnant?"

436
00:24:49.404 --> 00:24:54.201
And she said. "Well. I looked
in the mirror and my aura has changed."

437
00:24:54.910 --> 00:24:55.911
[dreamy music plays]

438
00:24:55.994 --> 00:24:57.287
"I just know it."

439
00:24:57.954 --> 00:24:59.873
"So how can I tell Wade?"

440
00:25:00.582 --> 00:25:03.293
[chuckles] And I said. "Well. you don't."

441
00:25:03.376 --> 00:25:06.338
"You don't tell Wade anything
until you know."

442
00:25:06.421 --> 00:25:07.422
She was convinced.

443
00:25:08.548 --> 00:25:12.093
One evening. she hits me with.
"I'm pretty sure I'm-- I'm pregnant."

444
00:25:13.553 --> 00:25:16.389
Angela took her to the doctor.
she got a test. and lo and behold.

445
00:25:16.473 --> 00:25:20.101
she come back out of there
with paperwork showing she was pregnant.

446
00:25:20.727 --> 00:25:25.774
She sent me a text message
and said. "I think I'm pregnant."

447
00:25:25.857 --> 00:25:27.192
And I was like. "Congratulations."

448
00:25:27.901 --> 00:25:30.779
[Connie] They announced
that she was pregnant.

449
00:25:30.862 --> 00:25:32.656
So I thought. "Okay."

450
00:25:32.739 --> 00:25:34.574
Wade was maybe a little nervous

451
00:25:34.658 --> 00:25:38.453
about what was fixing to come
and change his life. you know?

452
00:25:39.371 --> 00:25:41.706
I mean. I like to take stuff slow.
not just start jumping

453
00:25:41.790 --> 00:25:45.502
from dating one month
to all. "I'm already pregnant."

454
00:25:45.585 --> 00:25:48.171
But Roger was tickled to death.
Angela was happy.

455
00:25:48.255 --> 00:25:51.216
So if she's pregnant.
then I was good with it.

456
00:25:51.299 --> 00:25:56.638
She had said. "I want this baby
to call you Aunt Bae.

457
00:25:56.721 --> 00:25:58.640
Best Aunt Ever."

458
00:25:59.599 --> 00:26:02.519
So she actually went and had a shirt made.

459
00:26:04.646 --> 00:26:06.648
[Tiffany] I know that she was preparing.

460
00:26:06.731 --> 00:26:12.362
Like. we had a garage sale on the street.
and there was a high chair.

461
00:26:12.445 --> 00:26:15.031
And she was like.
"Oh. I want that high chair."

462
00:26:15.115 --> 00:26:18.243
We brought it over to her.
and she was excited to have it.

463
00:26:18.910 --> 00:26:21.871
[Wade] I've never had kids before.
so this was all a first for me.

464
00:26:21.955 --> 00:26:24.457
And she's already had two.
"You're the expert here."

465
00:26:24.541 --> 00:26:27.961
"I mean. I'm just gonna go
with whatever you're telling me."

466
00:26:28.545 --> 00:26:31.006
[Angela] I felt he was obligated.

467
00:26:31.840 --> 00:26:35.010
But I think the money
helped that obligation. [chuckles]

468
00:26:36.845 --> 00:26:38.722
[sparse. suspenseful music plays]

469
00:26:45.061 --> 00:26:47.063
[keyboard clacking]

470
00:26:51.151 --> 00:26:54.738
[Wade] She told Codey and Stephanie
that. uh. she wants to do a gender reveal.

471
00:26:54.821 --> 00:26:56.531
Double lines!

472
00:26:57.157 --> 00:26:58.241
[phone chimes]

473
00:27:03.371 --> 00:27:05.457
[Stephanie] I was like.
"Oh. wow. that's so exciting."

474
00:27:05.540 --> 00:27:06.875
But I had asked Codey one day.

475
00:27:06.958 --> 00:27:10.795
I'm like. "I don't think that she.
like. really has many friends."

476
00:27:11.338 --> 00:27:13.673
Because the way she acted towards me.

477
00:27:13.757 --> 00:27:16.176
Well. he actually was like.
"Just be nice."

478
00:27:16.259 --> 00:27:20.680
{\an8}"She really likes you.
so let's do it this day."

479
00:27:22.057 --> 00:27:27.020
She had a list of people
that she wanted to invite.

480
00:27:27.103 --> 00:27:29.439
I said. "So you're not…
your mom or anything?"

481
00:27:29.522 --> 00:27:32.400
She's like.
"No. don't mention it to my mom."

482
00:27:32.484 --> 00:27:36.655
"Nobody on… That's a no-go.
We don't do that."

483
00:27:37.489 --> 00:27:41.743
[Angela] Taylor was sending me the report
that was saying if it was a boy or a girl.

484
00:27:41.826 --> 00:27:44.371
And so I sent that on over to her friend.

485
00:27:44.454 --> 00:27:48.416
 [Stephanie] It said. "Congratulations.
Taylor Parker. it's a girl."

486
00:27:48.500 --> 00:27:51.252
And I'm. like. looking
at this paper really well.

487
00:27:51.336 --> 00:27:53.171
and I noticed the date on it.

488
00:27:53.254 --> 00:27:54.422
[suspenseful music plays]

489
00:27:54.506 --> 00:27:57.008
And the date on it said 2016.

490
00:27:57.717 --> 00:28:01.805
So I call her. and I said.
"Are you sure this is the right paper?"

491
00:28:01.888 --> 00:28:04.557
And she said.
"Let me call my doctor right now."

492
00:28:04.641 --> 00:28:08.061
Well. it seemed like 30 seconds
may have passed by.

493
00:28:08.144 --> 00:28:14.526
And she said. "There were over 200
or 100 misprints that day in the lab."

494
00:28:14.609 --> 00:28:19.030
"So they're gonna send a new one.
but she did say the gender is right."

495
00:28:21.658 --> 00:28:23.785
I knew something was off.

496
00:28:23.868 --> 00:28:26.538
-[people chatter indistinctly]
-[keyboard clacking]

497
00:28:30.959 --> 00:28:32.293
[people laugh and chatter]

498
00:28:34.421 --> 00:28:37.382
[people laugh heartily]

499
00:28:37.465 --> 00:28:38.967
[tender music plays]

500
00:28:39.050 --> 00:28:41.219
-[woman] So cute.
-[man] It's a little girl.

501
00:28:41.886 --> 00:28:45.515
[Stephanie] The day
of the gender reveal was very awkward.

502
00:28:45.598 --> 00:28:48.101
But she seemed really excited.

503
00:28:49.060 --> 00:28:51.646
She kind of. like. started
screaming and jumping up

504
00:28:51.730 --> 00:28:54.733
and. like. clapping.
and it was kind of quiet.

505
00:28:56.359 --> 00:28:57.986
They come around double-wide over there.

506
00:28:58.069 --> 00:29:00.530
they come around the side of the house
with a little calf.

507
00:29:00.613 --> 00:29:02.866
and it had a pink little bow
around its neck.

508
00:29:02.949 --> 00:29:06.202
You know? And they're all excited
and everything else. you know.

509
00:29:06.286 --> 00:29:08.079
and I just start clapping or whatnot.

510
00:29:08.163 --> 00:29:11.458
-[child 1] Show the cow who's the boss.
-[child 2] Oh. my God!

511
00:29:11.541 --> 00:29:14.419
I told her I always liked the name Clancy.

512
00:29:14.502 --> 00:29:19.299
So she come up
with the-- the middle name. Clancy Gaile.

513
00:29:20.717 --> 00:29:23.511
When he told me.
I was like. "Mmm." You know?

514
00:29:23.595 --> 00:29:25.805
"That's different." [chuckles]

515
00:29:25.889 --> 00:29:29.976
He said. "Mama. I've had that name
picked out for… for years."

516
00:29:30.560 --> 00:29:31.978
Y'all wanna get some pictures?

517
00:29:32.061 --> 00:29:34.105
[Codey] He was excited.
He was wanting to be a father.

518
00:29:34.189 --> 00:29:35.607
He always wanted to be a father.

519
00:29:35.690 --> 00:29:37.817
I mean. what man does not want
to be a father. you know?

520
00:29:37.901 --> 00:29:39.360
I don't know but a handful. maybe.

521
00:29:42.363 --> 00:29:45.492
[woman] I saw pictures
of this gender reveal.

522
00:29:45.575 --> 00:29:48.495
She had this baby calf
and had a pink bow around it.

523
00:29:48.578 --> 00:29:50.455
and it was a girl.

524
00:29:52.081 --> 00:29:54.250
{\an8}It made me sick. [chuckles]

525
00:29:54.334 --> 00:29:56.836
{\an8}It made me so sick to my stomach.

526
00:29:57.504 --> 00:29:58.838
{\an8}Because I knew.

527
00:29:58.922 --> 00:30:01.174
I mean. that she can't be pregnant.

528
00:30:01.257 --> 00:30:03.009
[dramatic music plays]

529
00:30:03.092 --> 00:30:05.428
She had a hysterectomy.

530
00:30:12.227 --> 00:30:15.271
[man] Our first involvement
with Taylor was in 2010.

531
00:30:15.355 --> 00:30:18.733
I think. at the age of 17.
for her first pregnancy.

532
00:30:19.234 --> 00:30:20.985
{\an8}After her second child.

533
00:30:21.069 --> 00:30:22.904
{\an8}she did not want to have
any more children.

534
00:30:22.987 --> 00:30:25.406
{\an8}so she made the decision
on permanent sterilization.

535
00:30:25.490 --> 00:30:26.950
physically blocking the tubes

536
00:30:27.033 --> 00:30:29.077
{\an8}so that you can't have children anymore.

537
00:30:29.160 --> 00:30:32.455
{\an8}She signed the appropriate consent forms.
went through the wait period.

538
00:30:32.539 --> 00:30:35.291
{\an8}and. uh. was still adamant
that that's what she wanted.

539
00:30:36.251 --> 00:30:38.628
Taylor came back
about a year and a half later

540
00:30:38.711 --> 00:30:39.712
with bleeding.

541
00:30:39.796 --> 00:30:42.382
She had a cyst on the right ovary.

542
00:30:42.882 --> 00:30:46.177
When we got inside.
she also had what looked like

543
00:30:46.261 --> 00:30:49.097
a visible ectopic pregnancy
in the left tube.

544
00:30:49.180 --> 00:30:51.474
An ectopic pregnancy
cannot be carried to term.

545
00:30:51.558 --> 00:30:54.644
It would be dangerous
and most likely life-threatening.

546
00:30:54.727 --> 00:30:56.729
The decision was made to do a hysterectomy

547
00:30:56.813 --> 00:30:59.148
and a removal of both tubes
and the right ovary.

548
00:30:59.232 --> 00:31:02.569
After a patient has had a hysterectomy.
she cannot become pregnant

549
00:31:02.652 --> 00:31:06.072
because she no longer
has a uterus to get pregnant from.

550
00:31:12.370 --> 00:31:14.372
[people chatter and laugh]

551
00:31:18.167 --> 00:31:20.169
[eerie music plays]

552
00:31:31.723 --> 00:31:32.891
[keyboard clacking]

553
00:31:43.443 --> 00:31:45.445
[keyboard clacking]

554
00:31:55.246 --> 00:31:58.833
[woman] This is a small town.
and she was a patient of ours.

555
00:31:58.917 --> 00:32:00.376
{\an8}In 2020.

556
00:32:00.460 --> 00:32:04.964
{\an8}we started seeing. uh.
social media posts about her pregnancy.

557
00:32:06.174 --> 00:32:09.218
[Dr. Mason] When we first found out
Taylor was saying she was pregnant

558
00:32:09.302 --> 00:32:10.929
and announced it on Facebook.

559
00:32:11.012 --> 00:32:14.807
we were very confused
because we knew that she could not be.

560
00:32:16.142 --> 00:32:21.105
We couldn't publicly say anything about it
because we were bound by privacy laws.

561
00:32:21.189 --> 00:32:25.109
Unless there is something
that's endangering someone else.

562
00:32:25.193 --> 00:32:26.903
then we can't break those HIPAA laws.

563
00:32:26.986 --> 00:32:30.073
We were being put
in a very difficult position.

564
00:32:36.621 --> 00:32:41.834
Me and Abby knew
she's not what she paints herself to be.

565
00:32:41.918 --> 00:32:43.962
[all chatter indistinctly]

566
00:32:44.045 --> 00:32:46.339
-[woman] Abby! [laughing]
-[Abby] Uh-uh!

567
00:32:46.422 --> 00:32:50.885
[McKenzie] And when I first met Taylor.
we hit it off immediately.

568
00:32:50.969 --> 00:32:55.765
She became a very close friend of mine.
I would say literally almost overnight.

569
00:32:55.848 --> 00:32:58.434
[ethereal music plays]

570
00:32:58.518 --> 00:33:02.939
{\an8}Before everything happened. Kenzie.
Taylor. and I were all best friends.

571
00:33:03.022 --> 00:33:05.942
And we would spend basically
all our time together.

572
00:33:06.025 --> 00:33:08.277
-Blah!
-[women laugh]

573
00:33:08.361 --> 00:33:12.615
[Abby] 24-7. If we weren't together.
there was at least two of us together.

574
00:33:13.700 --> 00:33:17.578
Our emotions were very connected.
If I was sad. she was sad.

575
00:33:17.662 --> 00:33:20.331
If she was sad. I was.
If she was happy. me too.

576
00:33:21.374 --> 00:33:23.543
{\an8}But I was worried bad for her.

577
00:33:23.626 --> 00:33:28.339
{\an8}As my close friend. I was so worried
because Taylor stayed sick.

578
00:33:28.423 --> 00:33:30.717
She stayed sick all the time.

579
00:33:31.342 --> 00:33:33.720
She had all these conditions.

580
00:33:34.303 --> 00:33:36.597
She was always in and out of the hospital.

581
00:33:36.681 --> 00:33:39.017
I remember there was
always pictures of her.

582
00:33:39.100 --> 00:33:41.561
like. in the hospital.
she was taking selfies.

583
00:33:42.937 --> 00:33:48.651
[McKenzie] Taylor told me
that she had been diagnosed with MS.

584
00:33:48.735 --> 00:33:51.654
She also had cancer.
from my understanding.

585
00:33:51.738 --> 00:33:55.283
At one time. she had had.
like. a brain tumor or something.

586
00:33:55.366 --> 00:33:56.951
She'd had a stroke.

587
00:33:57.035 --> 00:33:59.620
I mean. all of these things
kind of played into each other.

588
00:33:59.704 --> 00:34:01.539
There was a lot of posts about it.

589
00:34:01.622 --> 00:34:05.209
[McKenzie] She would actually have times
when you could see deficit

590
00:34:05.293 --> 00:34:06.544
from the stroke.

591
00:34:06.627 --> 00:34:09.213
You would see slurring. drooping face.

592
00:34:09.297 --> 00:34:13.885
I mean. I genuinely believed
that she had suffered a stroke.

593
00:34:13.968 --> 00:34:15.720
{\an8}[Abby] It's always something with Taylor.

594
00:34:15.803 --> 00:34:17.096
{\an8}She would put on Facebook

595
00:34:17.180 --> 00:34:19.223
{\an8}that she was either sick
or she had a headache.

596
00:34:19.307 --> 00:34:23.603
After it kept happening and happening
and happening over and over.

597
00:34:23.686 --> 00:34:26.564
I started being like.
"Yeah. maybe she's not really sick."

598
00:34:26.647 --> 00:34:28.858
"Maybe it's. like. something else."

599
00:34:29.692 --> 00:34:33.321
At the same time. I was going
through health problems of my own

600
00:34:33.404 --> 00:34:35.990
and was actually told
that I would never have kids naturally.

601
00:34:36.074 --> 00:34:38.284
{\an8}Taylor shared those emotions with me.

602
00:34:38.367 --> 00:34:41.162
{\an8}And then once she found out
that I was pregnant.

603
00:34:41.245 --> 00:34:43.206
it was like she was pregnant
with her own child.

604
00:34:43.289 --> 00:34:47.502
It was just so exciting for both of us.

605
00:34:49.128 --> 00:34:53.424
As my pregnancy progressed.
she wanted to be in everything.

606
00:34:53.508 --> 00:34:56.177
And as my best friend.
I was fine with that. you know?

607
00:34:56.260 --> 00:35:01.099
But then after Taylor had realized
McKenzie was having a girl.

608
00:35:01.182 --> 00:35:02.475
things got super weird.

609
00:35:03.059 --> 00:35:04.811
[Kenzie] She wanted
to plan the gender reveal.

610
00:35:04.894 --> 00:35:07.021
She wanted to be there
for the ultrasounds.

611
00:35:07.105 --> 00:35:09.065
She wanted to know
when the appointments were.

612
00:35:09.148 --> 00:35:11.484
How was Kenzie doing?
How was the baby doing?

613
00:35:11.567 --> 00:35:15.321
She wanted the login
to my pregnancy tracking app

614
00:35:15.404 --> 00:35:18.199
so that she could watch
the progress of my pregnancy.

615
00:35:18.783 --> 00:35:22.036
[Abby] It was concerning.
I mean. I know you're happy for her.

616
00:35:22.120 --> 00:35:24.580
but you don't have
to be. like. crazy happy.

617
00:35:24.664 --> 00:35:27.875
It's like she wanted
the pregnancy to be hers.

618
00:35:28.876 --> 00:35:32.338
And then she asked
if one of us could carry a baby for her.

619
00:35:32.880 --> 00:35:36.092
She said. "Okay. I've accepted
that I can't have any more kids."

620
00:35:36.968 --> 00:35:38.594
"Would one of y'all want to do it for me?"

621
00:35:39.178 --> 00:35:44.684
{\an8}She said that whoever carried this baby
would get a minimum of $50.000.

622
00:35:44.767 --> 00:35:46.435
But how could you have another baby

623
00:35:46.519 --> 00:35:49.438
when you didn't even take care
of the two kids you had?

624
00:35:49.522 --> 00:35:54.360
That was the first time I took
a step back from Taylor and was like…

625
00:35:55.778 --> 00:35:57.155
"You're scaring me."

626
00:35:58.156 --> 00:36:03.494
She became obsessive with my pregnancy.
and I had to cut her off.

627
00:36:05.079 --> 00:36:08.791
{\an8}Then I heard through her social media
that she was pregnant.

628
00:36:08.875 --> 00:36:11.169
that her and Wade were gonna have a baby.

629
00:36:12.253 --> 00:36:16.090
I feel like she got far enough away
from our friend group

630
00:36:16.174 --> 00:36:20.094
that she could start
this whole lie over again.

631
00:36:20.970 --> 00:36:23.347
He didn't know
that she'd had a hysterectomy.

632
00:36:29.437 --> 00:36:33.774
[Stephanie] After the gender reveal.
I call that lab.

633
00:36:33.858 --> 00:36:38.029
and I just said. "Hey. there was someone
I knew that went and had lab work done."

634
00:36:38.654 --> 00:36:40.823
and I read this lady
the gender reveal paper.

635
00:36:40.907 --> 00:36:44.577
and she said.
"We don't send things like that."

636
00:36:44.660 --> 00:36:48.789
I actually called the clinic.
and I spoke to the office manager.

637
00:36:48.873 --> 00:36:51.626
and she said. "If you don't mind
me asking. what's her name?"

638
00:36:51.709 --> 00:36:53.628
And I said. "Taylor Parker."

639
00:36:53.711 --> 00:36:55.713
With the HIPAA laws. I told her. I said.

640
00:36:55.796 --> 00:37:01.886
"I cannot give you any information
since she used to be a patient of ours."

641
00:37:01.969 --> 00:37:05.264
"But what all you've told me.
I can tell you this. just go with your…"

642
00:37:05.348 --> 00:37:07.433
"…gut. trust your instincts."

643
00:37:08.184 --> 00:37:09.894
And I left it at that.

644
00:37:09.977 --> 00:37:10.895
[gloomy music plays]

645
00:37:10.978 --> 00:37:13.064
[Stephanie] Me and Connie
are talking at this point.

646
00:37:13.147 --> 00:37:16.275
like. she has said so many things
that did not add up.

647
00:37:16.359 --> 00:37:20.613
She and I talked every day
about what she had learned or found out.

648
00:37:20.696 --> 00:37:23.366
and some of the clinics
she claimed to have gone to.

649
00:37:23.449 --> 00:37:26.327
and they wouldn't say.
but they would kind of say.

650
00:37:26.410 --> 00:37:29.372
"You're-- You're probably
on to something."

651
00:37:29.455 --> 00:37:31.916
I even asked Angela at the time. I said.

652
00:37:31.999 --> 00:37:35.127
"Did you go in with her
to Healthcare Express?"

653
00:37:35.753 --> 00:37:37.296
{\an8}She said. "No."

654
00:37:39.882 --> 00:37:42.760
[Codey] She would sit up in the bed.
eleven. twelve o'clock at night.

655
00:37:42.843 --> 00:37:44.762
you know. trying to investigate.

656
00:37:44.845 --> 00:37:46.681
You know. I would be nice at first. like.

657
00:37:46.764 --> 00:37:49.016
"Baby. what are you still doing up?"
You know?

658
00:37:49.100 --> 00:37:51.978
"Oh. I'm just scrolling through Taylor's…"

659
00:37:52.561 --> 00:37:54.855
Why in the fuck are you scrolling--
What the fuck?

660
00:37:54.939 --> 00:37:57.608
Gosh damn. leave that shit alone.

661
00:37:57.692 --> 00:37:58.943
I was like…

662
00:38:00.278 --> 00:38:01.654
"Am I crazy?"

663
00:38:01.737 --> 00:38:06.909
Like. "She wouldn't go through all this
to not be pregnant."

664
00:38:07.410 --> 00:38:12.206
The gender reveal. her dad was there.
her kids were there.

665
00:38:12.290 --> 00:38:14.709
I mean. you know. in your mind you think.

666
00:38:14.792 --> 00:38:18.170
"Well. why are they here
if it's not true?"

667
00:38:18.254 --> 00:38:20.172
I mean. they would know.

668
00:38:20.256 --> 00:38:24.135
[Stephanie] She's got to be pregnant
or somebody would say something.

669
00:38:28.973 --> 00:38:30.975
[hogs grunting]

670
00:38:36.856 --> 00:38:38.482
[hogs squeal]

671
00:38:43.654 --> 00:38:46.782
[suspenseful. chiming music plays]

672
00:38:48.743 --> 00:38:50.745
[keyboard clacking]

673
00:38:53.497 --> 00:38:55.249
-[calls hogs]
-[hogs squeal and grunt]

674
00:39:01.380 --> 00:39:05.259
[Wade] I started getting e-mails
and text messages while I was at work.

675
00:39:05.343 --> 00:39:07.845
It'd be from different numbers
that I didn't really know.

676
00:39:09.764 --> 00:39:12.183
Me and Taylor getting them
pretty much every day.

677
00:39:12.266 --> 00:39:14.477
I would get some
and then she would get some.

678
00:39:16.062 --> 00:39:19.899
This person was sending
text messages to him randomly

679
00:39:20.483 --> 00:39:22.777
throughout the day and night.

680
00:39:22.860 --> 00:39:26.364
{\an8}Not just one or two.
It'd be eight or ten a day or so.

681
00:39:26.447 --> 00:39:30.409
It was stuff that you would read.
like. "Who thinks like this?"

682
00:39:31.160 --> 00:39:32.078
Horrible thoughts.

683
00:39:32.161 --> 00:39:33.496
[keyboard clacking]

684
00:39:34.497 --> 00:39:38.667
[Angela] I got a-- a letter
in my business e-mail.

685
00:39:38.751 --> 00:39:41.879
That's when it really kind of started
getting involved in our life.

686
00:39:41.962 --> 00:39:44.715
It said.
"Listen. you know nothing about Taylor."

687
00:39:44.799 --> 00:39:46.967
"Don't try to be a mother figure to her."

688
00:39:47.051 --> 00:39:50.096
"See. I'm going to send her
in such a deep depression.

689
00:39:50.179 --> 00:39:53.224
{\an8}she'll probably try to kill herself
like she's tried before."

690
00:39:53.307 --> 00:39:57.269
{\an8}"But if not then.
me making Wade leave will do the trick."

691
00:39:58.145 --> 00:40:00.689
I told him. I said.
"Wade. there's something going on."

692
00:40:00.773 --> 00:40:03.025
"This is… This is not right."

693
00:40:03.109 --> 00:40:06.904
He finally called me one day and he said.
"Mama. here. look at these text messages."

694
00:40:11.367 --> 00:40:15.371
"We found out today
that her mother is behind that."

695
00:40:21.377 --> 00:40:25.464
One evening she called me on the phone
and she was terribly distraught.

696
00:40:25.548 --> 00:40:28.717
crying on the phone
and telling me this whole story

697
00:40:28.801 --> 00:40:31.470
about how her mother
had come back in the picture

698
00:40:31.554 --> 00:40:35.558
and caused all these problems for her.
and none of it was gonna work out.

699
00:40:35.641 --> 00:40:36.642
{\an8}[phone chimes]

700
00:40:37.893 --> 00:40:40.771
{\an8}[Renee] She was very distraught

701
00:40:40.855 --> 00:40:44.275
when she had to tell us
that… that wasn't gonna happen.

702
00:40:44.775 --> 00:40:46.902
She was not gonna be able to purchase.

703
00:40:47.695 --> 00:40:51.198
[Angela] Her mother had gone
supposedly in the bank prior

704
00:40:51.282 --> 00:40:54.660
and had all kinds of things changed
where then she couldn't get the money.

705
00:40:54.743 --> 00:40:55.703
[moody music plays]

706
00:40:55.786 --> 00:40:58.998
All of a sudden.
the mom's back in the picture.

707
00:40:59.081 --> 00:41:02.501
[chuckles dryly] And she had
orchestrated all that.

708
00:41:08.340 --> 00:41:10.676
[Wade] I told her.
"I can't believe your mom is doing this."

709
00:41:10.759 --> 00:41:13.137
"Can't believe you and your mom
can't come to some kinda peace

710
00:41:13.220 --> 00:41:14.513
on this whole deal."

711
00:41:15.848 --> 00:41:18.184
But once her mom found out
she was pregnant.

712
00:41:18.267 --> 00:41:21.145
she was just kind of against her having
any kind of kid with me

713
00:41:21.228 --> 00:41:23.939
that's gonna be getting
any kind of inheritance like that.

714
00:41:24.523 --> 00:41:27.943
She said. "I warned you
what kind of person she was."

715
00:41:29.195 --> 00:41:31.238
[Connie] It really upset him. you know.

716
00:41:31.322 --> 00:41:33.532
that he had to go back
and face his family.

717
00:41:33.616 --> 00:41:36.952
knowing that it wasn't ever gonna happen.

718
00:41:41.290 --> 00:41:43.834
{\an8}[Wade] Right in the middle
of everything else that was going on.

719
00:41:43.918 --> 00:41:47.463
{\an8}Taylor was portraying it more.
you know. happy-go-lucky family.

720
00:41:47.546 --> 00:41:49.465
{\an8}Like. "so many weeks pregnant."

721
00:41:49.548 --> 00:41:51.634
and have her hand
on her stomach or whatever.

722
00:41:55.137 --> 00:41:57.139
[keyboard clacking]

723
00:41:59.183 --> 00:42:01.519
[McKenzie] All people see is
the social media side of things.

724
00:42:01.602 --> 00:42:06.106
All they see is the happy smiling faces
and this loving. happy relationship.

725
00:42:09.026 --> 00:42:12.696
It revolved around Taylor.
She thrives off validation.

726
00:42:18.285 --> 00:42:21.580
[woman] I knew Taylor
from junior high to high school.

727
00:42:21.664 --> 00:42:24.625
She cared about the way she looked.
She cared about her weight.

728
00:42:24.708 --> 00:42:27.545
But she was very insecure.

729
00:42:27.628 --> 00:42:32.883
{\an8}Taylor would meet
most of the boys she spoke to online.

730
00:42:32.967 --> 00:42:38.639
She would ask girls
for pictures of themselves. neck down.

731
00:42:38.722 --> 00:42:40.516
But she had no shame in saying.

732
00:42:40.599 --> 00:42:43.602
like. "Oh. I'm sending it
to this guy I'm talking to."

733
00:42:43.686 --> 00:42:46.814
You know. they're thinking. like.
"You're just openly asking me

734
00:42:46.897 --> 00:42:48.440
to give you a nude picture of myself

735
00:42:48.524 --> 00:42:52.152
to send to some random person
to catfish them."

736
00:42:52.236 --> 00:42:55.573
Like. "Taylor!" Like. "What are they
going to do when they see you?"

737
00:42:57.324 --> 00:43:00.911
[McKenzie] Not long before I'd met her.
she'd lost a lot of weight.

738
00:43:01.412 --> 00:43:03.038
She had a…

739
00:43:03.956 --> 00:43:05.291
gastric sleeve done.

740
00:43:05.874 --> 00:43:08.669
She would say things
about how her skin looked

741
00:43:08.752 --> 00:43:12.673
and how she wished
that she could just take it off. you know.

742
00:43:12.756 --> 00:43:16.343
But then would get ready
and was so confident.

743
00:43:16.427 --> 00:43:18.637
You could not destroy her confidence.

744
00:43:20.723 --> 00:43:23.892
[Lindsey] I worked with Taylor
from 2018 to 2019.

745
00:43:25.311 --> 00:43:27.855
At the time.
I was the recruiting coordinator there.

746
00:43:27.938 --> 00:43:30.649
{\an8}She seemed like a good worker.
She seemed like she was on top of it.

747
00:43:30.733 --> 00:43:32.151
{\an8}She was eager to learn.

748
00:43:33.235 --> 00:43:36.071
{\an8}To be honest. I was going
through a very hard time.

749
00:43:36.155 --> 00:43:39.783
I'd just lost my youngest daughter
in February of '18.

750
00:43:39.867 --> 00:43:44.371
So I was doing good
to get up and go to work.

751
00:43:44.455 --> 00:43:46.290
[somber music plays]

752
00:43:46.373 --> 00:43:48.208
When I would have a hard day.

753
00:43:48.292 --> 00:43:51.253
you know. Taylor would talk
about how she had lost her baby girl too.

754
00:43:51.337 --> 00:43:53.255
you know. that was born with brain damage.

755
00:43:53.339 --> 00:43:57.426
And-- And so she really knew
what it was like to hold.

756
00:43:57.509 --> 00:44:00.387
you know. your child while they…

757
00:44:00.471 --> 00:44:05.351
[voice breaks] And so for another mom
to feel that. or another person.

758
00:44:05.434 --> 00:44:07.936
because you don't know how that feels
until you experience it.

759
00:44:08.020 --> 00:44:10.856
And it's… beyond devastating.

760
00:44:10.939 --> 00:44:16.654
And that's what would make me feel
like she understood and vice versa.

761
00:44:18.030 --> 00:44:20.240
But. of course. that wasn't true either.

762
00:44:22.117 --> 00:44:27.247
[McKenzie] She mimicked people
in all facets of life.

763
00:44:27.748 --> 00:44:32.336
I feel like she tried to mimic
a lot of what I went through too.

764
00:44:32.419 --> 00:44:37.591
It's almost like she has to piece together
parts of other people's real lives

765
00:44:37.675 --> 00:44:40.761
to make hers feel a little bit more real.

766
00:44:41.261 --> 00:44:43.764
You said you gave birth
to a baby that had brain damage

767
00:44:43.847 --> 00:44:46.392
that you held while dying.
like I did my daughter.

768
00:44:46.475 --> 00:44:48.102
and that was a lie.

769
00:44:48.185 --> 00:44:49.603
That was my daughter's story.

770
00:44:49.687 --> 00:44:52.564
That wasn't for her to use
to manipulate and lie.

771
00:44:52.648 --> 00:44:55.734
And it feels very. um. violating.

772
00:44:56.902 --> 00:44:58.404
Later. and only to find out

773
00:44:58.487 --> 00:45:01.824
that she actually was not doing
any of her job. really.

774
00:45:02.658 --> 00:45:05.661
Not scheduling appointments. really.
not inputting applications.

775
00:45:05.744 --> 00:45:10.624
She was using my job title in her e-mails.
unbeknownst to our boss.

776
00:45:10.708 --> 00:45:12.209
And that's when she was fired.

777
00:45:15.379 --> 00:45:19.091
At the same time. Taylor started
a side photography business.

778
00:45:19.174 --> 00:45:21.719
She would do it on the weekends.

779
00:45:21.802 --> 00:45:26.932
weddings. engagement announcements.
family portraits. happy moments.

780
00:45:27.015 --> 00:45:32.771
like family-oriented.
but happy. big. life-altering life events.

781
00:45:33.772 --> 00:45:37.067
It's like she wanted
to somehow be a part of.

782
00:45:37.568 --> 00:45:39.570
[solemn music plays]

783
00:45:43.198 --> 00:45:47.119
[woman 1] My daughter. Reagan.
had a photographer at her wedding.

784
00:45:47.661 --> 00:45:51.373
{\an8}I asked how. you know. how she came about
and what she had done before.

785
00:45:51.457 --> 00:45:54.293
{\an8}And she said one of her friends
had recommended her.

786
00:45:54.376 --> 00:45:56.712
and she was trying
to stay budget-friendly.

787
00:45:56.795 --> 00:46:00.424
so this person was ideal for that.

788
00:46:00.507 --> 00:46:01.884
Um. her name was Taylor Parker.

789
00:46:02.634 --> 00:46:06.013
{\an8}Very. uh. polite young lady.
you know. real…

790
00:46:06.096 --> 00:46:09.433
Pretty. uh-- She was a lot
like Reagan to me.

791
00:46:11.351 --> 00:46:12.853
[woman 2] The moments she captured

792
00:46:12.936 --> 00:46:15.939
of Reagan and the wedding
were absolutely beautiful.

793
00:46:16.023 --> 00:46:19.109
and Taylor made sure she greeted everybody

794
00:46:19.193 --> 00:46:22.780
{\an8}and told everyone who she was
and what she was doing there.

795
00:46:22.863 --> 00:46:24.239
And-- And it didn't feel

796
00:46:24.323 --> 00:46:27.993
like she was just some random stranger
none of us had ever met.

797
00:46:28.076 --> 00:46:30.412
Almost felt like she was a bridesmaid
at one point.

798
00:46:30.496 --> 00:46:32.122
'cause she was in all of our selfies.

799
00:46:32.706 --> 00:46:35.751
[Jessica] I asked about her.
"Who is she? Where is she from?"

800
00:46:35.834 --> 00:46:39.338
Reagan had mentioned that she was
going through some difficulties

801
00:46:39.421 --> 00:46:41.673
with her ex-husband.
I believe is what she said.

802
00:46:41.757 --> 00:46:45.844
She was just kind of having a hard time.
and Reagan was trying to include her

803
00:46:45.928 --> 00:46:47.846
to kind of take her mind off of that.

804
00:46:47.930 --> 00:46:51.517
So they had gotten close. closer.
you know. more acquainted

805
00:46:51.600 --> 00:46:53.060
throughout this process.

806
00:46:53.143 --> 00:46:57.314
and so Reagan invited her to hang out
with everybody after the reception.

807
00:46:57.397 --> 00:46:59.900
She made her feel
like just one of us girls.

808
00:47:01.401 --> 00:47:04.029
And I still look
at all of those photos today

809
00:47:04.112 --> 00:47:07.783
because of how spectacular that day was.

810
00:47:07.866 --> 00:47:09.993
and Taylor as a person.

811
00:47:10.077 --> 00:47:13.539
you would have never known her
to be any other way.

812
00:47:14.665 --> 00:47:16.291
[solemn music intensifies]

813
00:47:21.046 --> 00:47:22.881
-[clicks mouse]
-[music stops]

814
00:47:22.965 --> 00:47:25.634
[keyboard clacking]

815
00:47:29.346 --> 00:47:31.348
{\an8}[creepy music plays]

816
00:47:41.567 --> 00:47:42.776
[whirring]

817
00:47:57.708 --> 00:47:59.209
[music turns abrasive]

818
00:48:01.837 --> 00:48:04.089
[Wade] She would go
to a doctor appointment.

819
00:48:04.172 --> 00:48:07.551
{\an8}but I couldn't ever go in with her
because of COVID at the time.

820
00:48:07.634 --> 00:48:12.890
When I did try to go. she said the doctor
had an emergency or he couldn't meet us.

821
00:48:12.973 --> 00:48:14.641
Um. we had to reschedule.

822
00:48:14.725 --> 00:48:17.436
[interviewer] Was she starting
to look pregnant ever?

823
00:48:17.519 --> 00:48:19.021
[Connie] She gained weight.

824
00:48:19.104 --> 00:48:25.277
but the belly thing didn't seem
to. you know. really show that much.

825
00:48:25.360 --> 00:48:28.113
for the months that she claimed she was.

826
00:48:29.114 --> 00:48:32.534
But on Facebook or whatever.
and there was pictures.

827
00:48:39.583 --> 00:48:42.210
She came over where I was at.
She says. "Feel right here."

828
00:48:42.711 --> 00:48:44.338
And all of a sudden. the baby kicked.

829
00:48:46.882 --> 00:48:49.509
[Angela] I felt it. My husband felt it.

830
00:48:49.593 --> 00:48:52.638
And… why would you not believe it?

831
00:48:52.721 --> 00:48:55.182
Taylor had them two in her back pocket.

832
00:48:55.265 --> 00:48:57.935
Roger. he went hard on him. you know?
Like. "Man. you wanna step up?"

833
00:48:58.018 --> 00:49:00.187
"You gonna take care
of this woman and this baby?"

834
00:49:00.270 --> 00:49:01.480
"You know. 'cause it's yours."

835
00:49:01.563 --> 00:49:04.149
"My wife felt the baby moving
in your wife's belly."

836
00:49:05.567 --> 00:49:07.611
I would see a picture of her
or something like… "Ah."

837
00:49:07.694 --> 00:49:10.989
Steph would be like. "Look. I told--
Look. she's skinny this day. Look here."

838
00:49:12.115 --> 00:49:14.993
Five days ago. she looked
like she's gosh damn nine months pregnant.

839
00:49:16.995 --> 00:49:20.874
It was just some crazy jacked up junk
for sure. no doubt.

840
00:49:24.920 --> 00:49:28.256
[Wade] During that summer.
time together was very limited.

841
00:49:29.174 --> 00:49:32.177
She never hardly wanted ever me
to see her naked or anything

842
00:49:32.260 --> 00:49:35.514
because she said she was insecure
with her stretch marks.

843
00:49:36.723 --> 00:49:39.810
We never really did anything at all
pretty much.

844
00:49:40.519 --> 00:49:43.021
He said. "Man.
she won't let me. you know. touch her.

845
00:49:43.105 --> 00:49:44.982
get close with her. anything like that."

846
00:49:45.065 --> 00:49:49.569
He was like. "Codey. we ain't had sex
in four months. four to five months."

847
00:49:49.653 --> 00:49:51.196
I said. "Dude. what?"

848
00:49:51.279 --> 00:49:53.031
[tense music plays]

849
00:49:53.865 --> 00:49:55.784
[Wade] She'd go in the bathroom
and shut the door.

850
00:49:55.867 --> 00:49:58.328
and then she'd spend hours
doing just whatever.

851
00:50:01.415 --> 00:50:04.543
[Stephanie] Wade doing his own thing.
Like I said. it wasn't like he's the type

852
00:50:04.626 --> 00:50:07.421
that went to work. came home.
sat in the house. and they were together.

853
00:50:08.338 --> 00:50:11.383
Every single day.
he was doing something all the time.

854
00:50:13.343 --> 00:50:18.557
There was no space for him to sit down
and realize what was going on.

855
00:50:22.227 --> 00:50:23.353
[trackpad clicks]

856
00:50:27.482 --> 00:50:31.445
I mean. she had ultrasounds.
She had the fake belly.

857
00:50:31.528 --> 00:50:34.573
She had enough to make it believable.

858
00:50:36.283 --> 00:50:37.826
To her. it was just…

859
00:50:38.493 --> 00:50:40.203
"Whatever I gotta do."

860
00:50:41.246 --> 00:50:43.540
"Whatever I gotta do
to keep this man with me."

861
00:50:44.291 --> 00:50:47.044
["I Only Have Eyes for You"
by The Flamingos plays]

862
00:50:49.629 --> 00:50:54.217
<i>♪ My love must be a kind of blind love ♪</i>

863
00:50:57.471 --> 00:51:01.767
<i>♪ I can't see anyone but you ♪</i>

864
00:51:04.102 --> 00:51:05.353
<i>♪ Sha bop. sha bop ♪</i>

865
00:51:08.148 --> 00:51:09.274
<i>♪ Sha bop. sha bop ♪</i>

866
00:51:09.357 --> 00:51:10.901
[keyboard clacking]

867
00:51:12.194 --> 00:51:13.320
<i>♪ Sha bop. sha bop ♪</i>

868
00:51:16.114 --> 00:51:17.532
<i>♪ Sha bop. sha bop… ♪</i>

869
00:51:17.616 --> 00:51:19.493
[Kelly Mae May]
I'm a Western photographer.

870
00:51:19.576 --> 00:51:24.122
{\an8}I do. like. photography. like.
for Western people. seniors.

871
00:51:24.206 --> 00:51:29.419
{\an8}I do newborns. engagements.
I do maternity. weddings.

872
00:51:29.503 --> 00:51:32.172
I do do Western weddings only.

873
00:51:32.255 --> 00:51:37.886
Taylor Parker. she reached out to me
and wanted me to do a maternity session.

874
00:51:37.969 --> 00:51:39.679
{\an8}[Kelly Mae reads text message]

875
00:51:41.681 --> 00:51:43.934
"I'm a photographer myself

876
00:51:44.017 --> 00:51:47.395
and needing some Western-style
pregnancy couple pictures done."

877
00:51:47.479 --> 00:51:51.024
"I'd love to lay on the horse's back
with my belly in the air

878
00:51:51.108 --> 00:51:55.403
and have Wade holding the horse
looking at me. Just an idea."

879
00:51:56.404 --> 00:51:58.406
[spacey music plays]

880
00:52:01.910 --> 00:52:06.414
She was absolutely excited
about being pregnant.

881
00:52:07.415 --> 00:52:10.252
I felt like she liked
having her pictures taken.

882
00:52:10.335 --> 00:52:12.671
She felt very confident.

883
00:52:12.754 --> 00:52:16.675
She was super happy. excited.

884
00:52:18.760 --> 00:52:22.556
And I did a smoke bomb with my Watusi.

885
00:52:22.639 --> 00:52:25.350
And they acted like they were branding.

886
00:52:25.433 --> 00:52:29.020
It was pink.
And it was really neat looking.

887
00:52:30.522 --> 00:52:35.443
She said that she was ready
to get back to normal. back to her body.

888
00:52:35.527 --> 00:52:39.531
Like. she had just gained a lot of weight.
But she looked really good.

889
00:52:39.614 --> 00:52:41.867
I thought she looked very good.

890
00:52:42.576 --> 00:52:45.537
We actually had a really good time.

891
00:52:45.620 --> 00:52:48.456
We talked. We laughed.

892
00:52:48.540 --> 00:52:52.252
After they left.
I even told my husband. I was like.

893
00:52:52.335 --> 00:52:57.299
"Oh. my gosh. they're so nice.
She's so bubbly and friendly."

894
00:52:57.382 --> 00:52:59.593
Like. "They're such good people."

895
00:53:04.639 --> 00:53:06.141
[Stephanie] Now she's doing this.

896
00:53:07.350 --> 00:53:10.812
And I seen the pictures
and of course she looks big and pregnant.

897
00:53:11.813 --> 00:53:13.690
{\an8}Then my sister-in-law was like.

898
00:53:13.773 --> 00:53:17.152
"Oh. my gosh. you don't know this girl.
but her name is McKenzie Bright."

899
00:53:17.235 --> 00:53:20.447
"She knows Taylor.
You need to. like. message her."

900
00:53:20.530 --> 00:53:22.908
Stephanie had reached out to me

901
00:53:23.408 --> 00:53:26.286
and was like.
"Hey. I-- I need to know some things."

902
00:53:26.369 --> 00:53:30.415
She said. "Taylor cannot have kids.
She's had a hysterectomy."

903
00:53:30.498 --> 00:53:33.251
"There's no way she can
have a baby. period."

904
00:53:33.835 --> 00:53:36.338
"Nothing down there left for…" You know.

905
00:53:38.131 --> 00:53:39.216
I mean…

906
00:53:39.299 --> 00:53:40.342
[somber music plays]

907
00:53:40.425 --> 00:53:43.470
The word got out.
All the people that knew…

908
00:53:44.429 --> 00:53:46.598
started. you know.
within their own inner circles.

909
00:53:46.681 --> 00:53:48.600
going. "No. she can't be pregnant."

910
00:53:49.351 --> 00:53:53.939
But again. it was kind of her thing
to get just far enough away

911
00:53:54.022 --> 00:53:56.399
where "I can tell these lies again.

912
00:53:56.483 --> 00:53:59.903
but close enough
where I'm familiar with the person."

913
00:54:00.487 --> 00:54:03.490
But she got Reagan and stuck to her.

914
00:54:03.573 --> 00:54:04.908
[laughs]

915
00:54:04.991 --> 00:54:06.701
Stop videoing me!

916
00:54:08.536 --> 00:54:09.955
[Jessica] I can remember it vividly.

917
00:54:10.038 --> 00:54:11.873
We were walking out of the doctor's office

918
00:54:11.957 --> 00:54:14.751
and Reagan gets. um.
a message on her phone

919
00:54:14.834 --> 00:54:16.670
and she's just like. "Ugh."

920
00:54:16.753 --> 00:54:18.338
And I said. "Well. what's wrong?"

921
00:54:18.421 --> 00:54:21.007
She said. "Oh. people are
giving Taylor a hard time.

922
00:54:21.091 --> 00:54:23.134
trying to tell her
she's not really pregnant

923
00:54:23.218 --> 00:54:25.428
and that. you know. she's lying."

924
00:54:25.512 --> 00:54:27.681
And I was like. "Why?
Why would they do that?"

925
00:54:27.764 --> 00:54:30.141
She said. "I don't know. Mama."
She said. "It's just…"

926
00:54:30.225 --> 00:54:31.851
"You know how people are."

927
00:54:31.935 --> 00:54:33.353
If somebody needed somebody

928
00:54:33.436 --> 00:54:35.814
and nobody was there.
Reagan would be there.

929
00:54:35.897 --> 00:54:38.108
[intriguing music plays]

930
00:54:38.191 --> 00:54:41.987
When she first got pregnant
with her first daughter.

931
00:54:42.070 --> 00:54:43.822
she was 17.

932
00:54:44.447 --> 00:54:48.660
So it was hard for me at first.
You know. I was-- I was disappointed.

933
00:54:48.743 --> 00:54:49.995
{\an8}I was furious.

934
00:54:50.078 --> 00:54:54.582
{\an8}I was-- I was upset and I knew
that it could change your life

935
00:54:54.666 --> 00:54:57.711
and make starting a life a lot harder.

936
00:54:57.794 --> 00:55:00.338
I was over the moon about it 'cause…

937
00:55:00.422 --> 00:55:03.049
[inhales sharply] …we both loved babies.

938
00:55:04.009 --> 00:55:07.095
She's always wanted to be a mom
since she was little.

939
00:55:07.679 --> 00:55:10.890
It was like she was always meant
to be a mother. That was her thing.

940
00:55:10.974 --> 00:55:15.020
She was-- She was the best mother
that-- that I think I've ever met.

941
00:55:15.603 --> 00:55:18.064
[Jessica] She didn't care
that she was only 17.

942
00:55:18.148 --> 00:55:19.482
That wasn't in her mind.

943
00:55:19.566 --> 00:55:22.652
She wanted to be successful. of course.
but she wanted to be a mother.

944
00:55:22.736 --> 00:55:23.862
a successful mother.

945
00:55:23.945 --> 00:55:25.530
Here. It's an orange.

946
00:55:26.406 --> 00:55:28.533
[Reagan laughs]

947
00:55:28.616 --> 00:55:31.745
[Emily] After she had her baby girl.

948
00:55:31.828 --> 00:55:35.582
um. she. like. just came out
of her shell completely.

949
00:55:36.082 --> 00:55:39.085
And then she met Homer.

950
00:55:41.087 --> 00:55:42.839
[Jessica] I believe it was in May

951
00:55:42.922 --> 00:55:45.800
that she let us know
that she was pregnant again.

952
00:55:45.884 --> 00:55:48.845
And we were just over the moon
for her and Homer.

953
00:55:48.928 --> 00:55:52.724
And they were so excited.
You could just feel it in all of 'em.

954
00:55:53.350 --> 00:55:55.101
I said it's going to be a girl.

955
00:55:55.185 --> 00:55:58.355
[Reagan] Hey. what's in my belly?
What's in my belly?

956
00:55:58.438 --> 00:55:59.939
-[toddler] Baby.
-What kind of baby?

957
00:56:00.023 --> 00:56:01.691
[child] Is it a brother or sister?

958
00:56:01.775 --> 00:56:02.734
[toddler] Sister.

959
00:56:02.817 --> 00:56:03.943
-[all laugh]
-[woman] Yeah!

960
00:56:04.027 --> 00:56:05.487
[Reagan] A sister!

961
00:56:08.239 --> 00:56:09.616
[Connie] By that time.

962
00:56:09.699 --> 00:56:12.702
none of us had any idea
what she was gonna do.

963
00:56:13.578 --> 00:56:17.457
At some point.
she's gonna have to fake a miscarriage.

964
00:56:17.540 --> 00:56:19.709
I mean. that's the only way out of this.

965
00:56:19.793 --> 00:56:22.170
She'd say. you know.
"I lost the baby today." and…

966
00:56:22.879 --> 00:56:25.673
that would be. you know. the end of it.

967
00:56:25.757 --> 00:56:27.425
But that never came.

968
00:56:27.509 --> 00:56:29.511
[bold. suspenseful music plays]

969
00:56:30.720 --> 00:56:35.558
I heard of the hysterectomy and all that.
but I had nothing in writing.

970
00:56:35.642 --> 00:56:38.812
nothing from a doctor.
nothing to present to him to say.

971
00:56:38.895 --> 00:56:41.064
"Look. this is all a lie."

972
00:56:41.815 --> 00:56:45.151
Well. I would put questions in his mind.
He would listen to me.

973
00:56:45.235 --> 00:56:47.904
He would relay the questions I had to her.

974
00:56:47.987 --> 00:56:49.989
but she always had a counter.

975
00:56:50.073 --> 00:56:52.409
To everything I presented.
she countered it.

976
00:56:53.034 --> 00:56:56.037
So it was a tug-of-war between she and I.

977
00:56:56.538 --> 00:56:59.457
She said. "I just don't think
your mom wants us to be happy."

978
00:56:59.541 --> 00:57:01.167
"She probably don't trust me."

979
00:57:01.251 --> 00:57:04.921
She said. "But I'll make sure
that all this works out in the end."

980
00:57:05.004 --> 00:57:08.091
[Stephanie] Connie don't want
Wade to be upset with her.

981
00:57:08.174 --> 00:57:10.885
so she kind of backed off.
and I was like. "Well. I don't care."

982
00:57:11.678 --> 00:57:16.182
I ended up just saying. "All this stuff
that you have told me has been a lie."

983
00:57:16.266 --> 00:57:18.810
When I hit her with everything
is when she said.

984
00:57:18.893 --> 00:57:21.604
"Well. let me tell you
how all this happened."

985
00:57:22.939 --> 00:57:27.610
She blamed her mother
for all of the things that she'd done.

986
00:57:27.694 --> 00:57:28.736
[phone chimes]

987
00:57:32.907 --> 00:57:33.867
[phone chimes]

988
00:57:33.950 --> 00:57:36.744
None of it made sense.
If she didn't want you to be pregnant.

989
00:57:36.828 --> 00:57:39.664
why would she hire somebody
to fake an ultrasound?

990
00:57:39.747 --> 00:57:40.999
[phone chimes]

991
00:57:43.042 --> 00:57:45.837
But everything I would say.
she had something to say.

992
00:57:45.920 --> 00:57:48.465
even though she sounded like a… idiot.

993
00:57:51.551 --> 00:57:53.094
[birds chirp]

994
00:57:53.178 --> 00:57:56.639
I had talked to somebody
that knew Taylor's aunt.

995
00:57:58.433 --> 00:58:00.643
The aunt gave me Taylor's mom's number.

996
00:58:00.727 --> 00:58:01.811
[tense music plays]

997
00:58:01.895 --> 00:58:02.812
[phone rings]

998
00:58:03.396 --> 00:58:06.649
And her mom said.
"I've been waiting on this phone call."

999
00:58:06.733 --> 00:58:08.610
[pulsing. moody music plays]

1000
00:58:08.693 --> 00:58:13.490
She said. "Taylor cannot have kids.
She's had a hysterectomy."

1001
00:58:13.573 --> 00:58:14.908
"No. we don't have money."

1002
00:58:14.991 --> 00:58:17.619
"There is no inheritance money."

1003
00:58:17.702 --> 00:58:20.497
"There is no money at all anywhere."

1004
00:58:20.580 --> 00:58:22.582
I called Connie.
I'm like. "I talked to her mom."

1005
00:58:22.665 --> 00:58:26.336
It wasn't anything new.
that she'd always. always been a liar.

1006
00:58:27.378 --> 00:58:32.675
That's when I said. "Why are you
not telling Wade or somebody?"

1007
00:58:32.759 --> 00:58:35.637
And that's when the granddaughter
came in play.

1008
00:58:37.931 --> 00:58:41.684
She was terrified.
because if she were to tell.

1009
00:58:41.768 --> 00:58:45.813
Taylor would pull that granddaughter away.

1010
00:58:45.897 --> 00:58:48.942
and she would never. ever be able
to see that little girl again.

1011
00:58:49.943 --> 00:58:53.279
She was scared to say anything.

1012
00:58:56.157 --> 00:58:57.617
I had called him.

1013
00:58:57.700 --> 00:59:01.329
I said. "Wade. she is not pregnant.
She cannot have kids."

1014
00:59:01.913 --> 00:59:03.915
And he said. "Stephanie. yes. she can."

1015
00:59:03.998 --> 00:59:07.544
"Her mom's lying to you."
Like. "Her mom's crazy."

1016
00:59:07.627 --> 00:59:09.921
Um. "She does all this stuff.
She's. like. crazy."

1017
00:59:10.004 --> 00:59:11.881
I'm like. "Wade. no.
you don't understand." Like…

1018
00:59:11.965 --> 00:59:14.926
"Taylor was in the hospital for this.
She had a hysterectomy."

1019
00:59:15.009 --> 00:59:16.886
And he was like.
"Her mom's just telling you--"

1020
00:59:16.970 --> 00:59:18.846
"There's no belly there.
She has no stomach."

1021
00:59:18.930 --> 00:59:20.807
He was talking. I was talking over him.

1022
00:59:20.890 --> 00:59:24.602
"Man. all this is bullshit.
This bitch is fucking you. dude."

1023
00:59:24.686 --> 00:59:28.773
"She ain't got this money.
She… I mean. this is a fucking scandal."

1024
00:59:28.856 --> 00:59:31.568
And I told him. I said-- I started--
I kinda got teary-eyed. you know?

1025
00:59:31.651 --> 00:59:34.112
'Cause I was one
of his closest friends. you know?

1026
00:59:34.946 --> 00:59:36.781
I just-- I ain't about the drama.

1027
00:59:36.864 --> 00:59:39.492
I don't care what other folks do.
I'm-- Nah-uh.

1028
00:59:40.785 --> 00:59:42.996
I kind of just washed my hands. you know.

1029
00:59:44.497 --> 00:59:48.668
Him and Codey kind of…
They quit speaking after that.

1030
00:59:48.751 --> 00:59:50.003
[dog barks in distance]

1031
00:59:51.963 --> 00:59:52.839
I'm like…

1032
00:59:54.841 --> 00:59:56.009
"Now what?"

1033
01:00:01.014 --> 01:00:03.016
[Taylor] Look at it. trying to walk.

1034
01:00:03.099 --> 01:00:05.310
[exclaims happily]

1035
01:00:05.393 --> 01:00:07.186
Oh. my goodness.

1036
01:00:08.271 --> 01:00:09.522
[cow lows]

1037
01:00:09.606 --> 01:00:11.816
She's not wanting to let it suckle.

1038
01:00:13.735 --> 01:00:15.028
[cow lows]

1039
01:00:15.111 --> 01:00:16.404
Uh-oh.

1040
01:00:18.740 --> 01:00:19.741
[anxious music plays]

1041
01:00:19.824 --> 01:00:21.409
[keyboard clacking]

1042
01:00:28.124 --> 01:00:33.421
[McKenzie] And my mind constantly wandered
and just raced and raced and raced with…

1043
01:00:34.797 --> 01:00:36.007
"What is she gonna do?"

1044
01:00:44.891 --> 01:00:46.976
[Tiffany] We're all watching
this house like hawks.

1045
01:00:47.060 --> 01:00:50.063
Like. "What-- What is gonna happen?
What is she gonna do?"

1046
01:00:52.899 --> 01:00:58.321
As the time went on. it got
closer and closer to her "due date."

1047
01:00:58.404 --> 01:01:00.365
and it didn't happen.

1048
01:01:01.866 --> 01:01:05.620
[Wade] She had a lot of factors
of why she could have missed her due date.

1049
01:01:05.703 --> 01:01:08.790
She wasn't eating right.
or it might have been not ready yet.

1050
01:01:08.873 --> 01:01:13.127
or the baby might be too small.
but I didn't really know what to believe.

1051
01:01:13.836 --> 01:01:15.004
[keyboard clacking]

1052
01:01:17.965 --> 01:01:22.387
We all knew that there was no way
for her to have a miscarriage anymore.

1053
01:01:25.765 --> 01:01:29.686
[Dr. Mason] We felt that she had
to come up with a baby somehow.

1054
01:01:30.311 --> 01:01:33.690
So for the safety of the rest
of our patients and our nursery.

1055
01:01:33.773 --> 01:01:37.026
we did alert the hospital
to be on higher alert.

1056
01:01:37.110 --> 01:01:38.945
what was called Code Pink.

1057
01:01:39.821 --> 01:01:45.660
We really thought that. if anything.
she would just try to steal a baby.

1058
01:01:47.370 --> 01:01:49.539
[Taylor] <i>♪ Rain. baby. rain! ♪</i>

1059
01:01:55.670 --> 01:01:58.715
[Connie] And at that point.
she went ten months.

1060
01:01:58.798 --> 01:02:01.509
and I thought.
"That doesn't happen either."

1061
01:02:02.176 --> 01:02:04.303
"Never heard of that in my life."

1062
01:02:07.014 --> 01:02:08.641
[Tiffany] I lived across from Wade.

1063
01:02:08.725 --> 01:02:12.520
and I had taken pictures of her
and Wade out in the driveway.

1064
01:02:12.603 --> 01:02:16.232
She didn't look pregnant
for being ten months pregnant. you know?

1065
01:02:16.315 --> 01:02:21.237
I mean. it started
to become not believable.

1066
01:02:22.530 --> 01:02:26.033
And that's when all
of these weird events started happening.

1067
01:02:27.285 --> 01:02:28.453
[insects chirp]

1068
01:02:28.536 --> 01:02:31.164
[keyboard clacking]

1069
01:02:31.247 --> 01:02:33.875
[Wade] I'd done taken off leave
from my work.

1070
01:02:33.958 --> 01:02:37.336
and she had scheduled
an appointment with Mount Pleasant.

1071
01:02:38.755 --> 01:02:42.008
She wakes me up and says she smells smoke.

1072
01:02:42.091 --> 01:02:44.177
So I get up and walk outside.

1073
01:02:44.260 --> 01:02:47.054
and the whole underside
of my house is on fire.

1074
01:02:47.138 --> 01:02:48.473
[dramatic music plays]

1075
01:02:48.556 --> 01:02:53.186
So I just took my water hose.
put what fire was left burning out.

1076
01:02:53.269 --> 01:02:56.481
She was gonna have the baby that day.
and I think Wade even took off work.

1077
01:02:56.564 --> 01:02:58.399
So it got down to.
"I've gotta do something."

1078
01:03:01.194 --> 01:03:04.614
There was no doubt in my mind that…
I mean. I knew she did that.

1079
01:03:05.364 --> 01:03:07.575
I said. "I'm gonna sleep
on the couch for now."

1080
01:03:07.658 --> 01:03:09.494
Then whenever I got up about 7:00.

1081
01:03:09.577 --> 01:03:12.371
she said. "Hey. I know you're
probably upping to get ready to go.

1082
01:03:12.455 --> 01:03:14.415
but we can't go
to Mount Pleasant this morning."

1083
01:03:14.499 --> 01:03:16.167
"There's been a bomb threat called in."

1084
01:03:16.959 --> 01:03:18.503
[man] <i>Mount Pleasant Police Department.</i>

1085
01:03:18.586 --> 01:03:19.879
[woman] <i>I just received a caller.</i>

1086
01:03:19.962 --> 01:03:22.632
<i>and he said</i>
<i>there is a bomb in the hospital.</i>

1087
01:03:23.299 --> 01:03:26.844
[man] <i>Okay. so a male subject called</i>
<i>and said there was a bomb in the hospital?</i>

1088
01:03:26.928 --> 01:03:27.929
[woman] <i>Yes. sir. He said…</i>

1089
01:03:28.012 --> 01:03:30.556
[Wade] "There is no way. Taylor.
that there's a bomb threat."

1090
01:03:30.640 --> 01:03:33.017
And she said. "No. look on Facebook.
It's all over Facebook."

1091
01:03:34.477 --> 01:03:37.939
[Connie] And she said. "They had
a bomb threat this morning." [chuckles]

1092
01:03:38.022 --> 01:03:40.775
There was a bomb threat. Sure was.

1093
01:03:40.858 --> 01:03:42.151
'Cause you called it in!

1094
01:03:42.235 --> 01:03:44.237
[dramatic music plays]

1095
01:03:47.698 --> 01:03:49.784
I worried about his safety.

1096
01:03:49.867 --> 01:03:52.787
All I cared about was him at that point.

1097
01:03:52.870 --> 01:03:54.914
and his well-being.

1098
01:03:55.498 --> 01:03:59.043
I said. "Do you love her?"
"Well. I care about her."

1099
01:03:59.126 --> 01:04:03.923
I said. "But do you love her?"
"Well. not really. I just. you know…"

1100
01:04:04.006 --> 01:04:05.883
And I said. "Then get her gone."

1101
01:04:05.967 --> 01:04:08.636
Found out later.
he really pinned her down.

1102
01:04:08.719 --> 01:04:12.056
and he really got harsh with her.
like. "Enough already."

1103
01:04:12.682 --> 01:04:15.518
[Wade] I don't know
if I've ever seen her that mad before.

1104
01:04:15.601 --> 01:04:17.645
She said. "I'm tired of your family

1105
01:04:17.728 --> 01:04:21.023
not siding with us
on me having your baby."

1106
01:04:21.107 --> 01:04:24.235
"I'd be dang if they want to call me
a liar and say I'm not pregnant."

1107
01:04:24.318 --> 01:04:26.571
"I'm gonna show everybody
that I'm pregnant."

1108
01:04:27.405 --> 01:04:29.198
"I'm gonna bring a kid home."

1109
01:04:30.074 --> 01:04:31.868
{\an8}Exactly what she said.

1110
01:04:55.141 --> 01:04:56.100
[keyboard clacking]

1111
01:05:01.522 --> 01:05:02.732
[ominous music plays]

1112
01:05:12.617 --> 01:05:14.619
[keyboard clacking]

1113
01:05:17.830 --> 01:05:22.168
[Jessica] On that Wednesday.
Reagan and Taylor had had a girls' day.

1114
01:05:22.251 --> 01:05:25.379
They went to Starbucks apparently
and just kind of hung out.

1115
01:05:25.463 --> 01:05:26.339
[phone chimes]

1116
01:05:27.673 --> 01:05:30.217
And then on the 8th.

1117
01:05:30.301 --> 01:05:32.762
Taylor had come back over
to talk with Reagan.

1118
01:05:32.845 --> 01:05:35.014
Apparently. she was just coming to visit.

1119
01:05:35.097 --> 01:05:38.893
She was expecting to be going in
to be induced the next day.

1120
01:05:38.976 --> 01:05:43.314
And Reagan felt like Taylor
was probably overwhelmed with everything.

1121
01:05:43.397 --> 01:05:46.275
And she was trying to be
that one person there for her

1122
01:05:46.359 --> 01:05:47.652
when nobody else was.

1123
01:05:47.735 --> 01:05:49.195
[suspenseful music plays]

1124
01:05:52.949 --> 01:05:54.951
[keyboard clacking]

1125
01:05:58.955 --> 01:06:02.083
[Wade] I got dressed that morning
about 3:30 or 4:00.

1126
01:06:02.166 --> 01:06:05.836
We had a pen full of hogs that I had done
gathered up or bought from other trappers.

1127
01:06:07.964 --> 01:06:12.510
The plan was we were
both supposed to go load the hogs up.

1128
01:06:12.593 --> 01:06:13.678
go drop 'em off.

1129
01:06:13.761 --> 01:06:17.181
and then we were gonna swing down
to the Idabel Hospital.

1130
01:06:17.264 --> 01:06:18.724
I said. "Are you ready to leave?"

1131
01:06:18.808 --> 01:06:21.477
And she said.
"Well. I'm not feeling just too great."

1132
01:06:21.560 --> 01:06:24.480
"I think I'm gonna
let you leave with the hogs.

1133
01:06:24.563 --> 01:06:27.191
and then I'm going to meet you
at the hospital."

1134
01:06:27.274 --> 01:06:30.486
I said. "Well. that wasn't the plan.
I think we both need to go together."

1135
01:06:30.569 --> 01:06:31.404
"This is a big deal."

1136
01:06:31.487 --> 01:06:35.366
She said. "Nah. we need to get them sold.
That's too much money to turn down."

1137
01:06:35.449 --> 01:06:37.827
So I didn't argue with her no more.

1138
01:06:37.910 --> 01:06:40.830
{\an8}I went and loaded the hogs up. and I left.

1139
01:06:40.913 --> 01:06:42.915
{\an8}[suspenseful music intensifies]

1140
01:06:44.250 --> 01:06:46.627
It probably took me
four and a half hours or something

1141
01:06:46.711 --> 01:06:48.587
to get up there from my house.

1142
01:06:48.671 --> 01:06:51.173
I pulled in. and he told me. he said.

1143
01:06:51.257 --> 01:06:53.676
"I didn't order--
I didn't order no hogs today."

1144
01:06:53.759 --> 01:06:56.053
I said. "There's no way.
You texted me this morning."

1145
01:06:56.137 --> 01:06:57.221
[phone chimes]

1146
01:06:58.681 --> 01:07:00.057
He said. "I didn't text nobody."

1147
01:07:00.141 --> 01:07:03.144
I said. "You didn't text me
from this number?" I pulled out my phone.

1148
01:07:04.020 --> 01:07:05.980
He said. "That's not my number."

1149
01:07:06.063 --> 01:07:08.607
I said. "Did you not talk
to Taylor about some hogs?"

1150
01:07:08.691 --> 01:07:10.026
He said. "Yeah. weeks ago."

1151
01:07:10.109 --> 01:07:12.987
"I quit texting her." And he said.
"I didn't follow up with nothing."

1152
01:07:13.070 --> 01:07:16.449
I said. "Well. who in the world
would've texted me from this number then?"

1153
01:07:16.532 --> 01:07:18.034
He said. "Man. I don't know."

1154
01:07:18.117 --> 01:07:19.368
[telephone rings]

1155
01:07:20.953 --> 01:07:22.455
[Jessica] I went to work.

1156
01:07:22.538 --> 01:07:25.207
I was in my office. and Homer called me.

1157
01:07:25.291 --> 01:07:28.210
He said. "Miss Jessica.
have you talked to Reagan this morning?"

1158
01:07:28.294 --> 01:07:29.378
I said. "No."

1159
01:07:29.462 --> 01:07:30.421
He said. "Well.

1160
01:07:31.547 --> 01:07:35.926
she's texting me. but it's…
It doesn't… It's not like her."

1161
01:07:36.010 --> 01:07:37.762
And I was like. "Well. what do you mean?"

1162
01:07:37.845 --> 01:07:40.973
He said. "Well. after she stopped texting.
I've been trying to call her.

1163
01:07:41.057 --> 01:07:42.141
and she won't answer."

1164
01:07:42.224 --> 01:07:44.935
I said. "Is she at work?"
He said. "They haven't heard from her."

1165
01:07:45.895 --> 01:07:49.565
[Marcus] It was my day off from work.
My friend Chris had come over.

1166
01:07:49.648 --> 01:07:51.442
Uh. I mean. it just seemed
like a normal day.

1167
01:07:51.525 --> 01:07:55.196
And then Jessica called me
and said that Reagan wasn't answering.

1168
01:07:55.279 --> 01:07:58.741
I said. "Well. we're fixing to go
to town anyway. I'll head that way."

1169
01:08:00.117 --> 01:08:02.453
We were about halfway there.
and she called me back.

1170
01:08:02.536 --> 01:08:04.789
and said our grandbaby's
not at the daycare.

1171
01:08:04.872 --> 01:08:06.415
She sounded frantic.

1172
01:08:06.499 --> 01:08:08.209
So she headed to the house.

1173
01:08:09.710 --> 01:08:12.630
[Jessica] As I'm getting to Reagan's road
and turn onto it.

1174
01:08:12.713 --> 01:08:15.841
I see their house.
and the garage door is open.

1175
01:08:16.342 --> 01:08:17.927
Well. that worried me.

1176
01:08:18.010 --> 01:08:20.805
because they never leave
their garage door open.

1177
01:08:20.888 --> 01:08:23.265
As I get out of my car.

1178
01:08:23.349 --> 01:08:27.019
I'm walking.
and I see these little red streaks.

1179
01:08:27.103 --> 01:08:29.605
And I thought.
"Well. the dog must have hurt its foot."

1180
01:08:29.688 --> 01:08:31.649
And so that's what I was seeing.

1181
01:08:32.650 --> 01:08:37.488
And I kind of opened the door.
and I saw a bloody footprint.

1182
01:08:38.656 --> 01:08:40.241
And I shut the door.

1183
01:08:40.324 --> 01:08:42.409
And as I kinda stepped back.
and I thought.

1184
01:08:42.493 --> 01:08:44.787
"No. if she's in there and she's hurt

1185
01:08:44.870 --> 01:08:49.125
or. you know. she can't answer me.
I need to go in."

1186
01:08:51.001 --> 01:08:53.295
[woman] <i>New Boston. 911.</i>
<i>What's your emergency?</i>

1187
01:08:53.379 --> 01:08:56.257
[Jessica wailing]

1188
01:08:56.340 --> 01:08:59.176
-[woman] <i>Ma'am. Ma'am?</i>
-[Jessica wails]

1189
01:08:59.260 --> 01:09:02.346
{\an8}<i>Help me. My daughter's been murdered.</i>

1190
01:09:02.429 --> 01:09:04.473
{\an8}[woman] <i>Okay. where are you located at?</i>

1191
01:09:04.557 --> 01:09:08.477
[Jessica] <i>At… </i>[beeps] Street. [beeps]

1192
01:09:08.561 --> 01:09:10.104
{\an8}-[woman] <i>In New Boston?</i>
-[Jessica] <i>Yeah.</i>

1193
01:09:10.187 --> 01:09:11.438
{\an8}[woman] <i>What happened?</i>

1194
01:09:11.522 --> 01:09:13.858
{\an8}[Jessica] <i>I don't know.</i>
<i>Somebody got in her house.</i>

1195
01:09:13.941 --> 01:09:15.943
<i>-She's dead!</i>
-[woman] <i>Okay.</i>

1196
01:09:16.026 --> 01:09:18.404
[Jessica] <i>She's dead! </i>[echoes]

1197
01:09:20.406 --> 01:09:21.490
[car door closes]

1198
01:09:23.909 --> 01:09:26.453
[Taylor] No. I can't.
There's something wrong with her.

1199
01:09:27.371 --> 01:09:29.373
-[trooper] What's wrong. ma'am?
-I had my baby.

1200
01:09:29.456 --> 01:09:32.209
And I'm trying to get to Idabel Hospital
where my husband--

1201
01:09:32.293 --> 01:09:34.837
-[trooper] Idabel?
-Yeah. my husband's up there.

1202
01:09:35.462 --> 01:09:38.299
He was delivering hogs
right outside of Idabel.

1203
01:09:38.382 --> 01:09:41.260
That's why I was trying to get to him.
Can you call my husband?

1204
01:09:42.094 --> 01:09:44.638
-[trooper] Yes.
-[man on phone] <i>How old's the baby. ma'am?</i>

1205
01:09:44.722 --> 01:09:48.058
The baby's only. like.
maybe 35 minutes old.

1206
01:09:48.142 --> 01:09:50.102
[trooper] I'm gonna give
the phone back to her.

1207
01:09:50.811 --> 01:09:53.355
[dispatch] <i>She was flying down the road.</i>
<i>You stopped her or what?</i>

1208
01:09:53.439 --> 01:09:55.983
[trooper] She was driving down the road.
passing on the shoulder.

1209
01:09:56.066 --> 01:09:59.028
She had her hazards on.
She ran over a bird.

1210
01:09:59.111 --> 01:10:00.946
It's still on-- uh. in the grille here.

1211
01:10:01.030 --> 01:10:03.032
[eerie music plays]

1212
01:10:03.824 --> 01:10:05.826
Did a name come back on that 27?
Her name's Taylor.

1213
01:10:05.910 --> 01:10:07.453
I don't have her last name.

1214
01:10:09.371 --> 01:10:13.083
[dispatch] <i>Uh. the car is r-- registered</i>
<i>to Wade Griffin.</i>

1215
01:10:13.834 --> 01:10:16.670
[trooper] I think he's already
in Oklahoma. uh. working.

1216
01:10:17.421 --> 01:10:18.964
So he's already…

1217
01:10:19.048 --> 01:10:20.299
[Wade] She called me.

1218
01:10:20.883 --> 01:10:23.636
She said she's having the baby
on the side of the road.

1219
01:10:24.386 --> 01:10:26.805
How quick could I get to the hospital?

1220
01:10:27.389 --> 01:10:29.099
{\an8}-[Wade on phone] <i>Hello?</i>
-Where you at?

1221
01:10:29.683 --> 01:10:33.437
{\an8}[Wade on phone] <i>I'm trying-- I'm trying</i>
<i>to get these. um. these hogs moved.</i>

1222
01:10:33.520 --> 01:10:34.480
{\an8}<i>What's up?</i>

1223
01:10:34.980 --> 01:10:39.318
{\an8}We're-- We're going to the hospital.
We're going to Titus.

1224
01:10:41.654 --> 01:10:44.156
[Wade] <i>All right. well.</i>
<i>let me finish what I'm doing.</i>

1225
01:10:44.240 --> 01:10:45.658
<i>I'll call you right back.</i>

1226
01:10:46.325 --> 01:10:47.451
Okay?

1227
01:10:47.534 --> 01:10:48.744
[Wade on phone] <i>All right. Bye.</i>

1228
01:10:48.827 --> 01:10:49.995
I'm sorry.

1229
01:10:50.079 --> 01:10:51.997
I was like. "This has got to be a joke."

1230
01:10:52.081 --> 01:10:55.417
[medic] So you was-- you was on your way
to Idabel to have the baby?

1231
01:10:55.501 --> 01:10:56.710
-[Taylor] Yeah.
-[medic] Okay.

1232
01:10:56.794 --> 01:10:59.213
-[Taylor blubbering]
-[medic] Okay. It's all right.

1233
01:10:59.296 --> 01:11:01.757
Just relax. darling. [speaks indistinctly]

1234
01:11:01.840 --> 01:11:03.717
[siren wails]

1235
01:11:03.801 --> 01:11:05.803
[man speaks indistinctly on radio]

1236
01:11:11.934 --> 01:11:14.311
[Jessica sobbing] <i>Reagan! Reagan!</i>

1237
01:11:14.395 --> 01:11:16.814
{\an8}When we pull up.
Jessica's in the driveway.

1238
01:11:16.897 --> 01:11:20.192
{\an8}She's on her hands and knees.
and she's just screaming.

1239
01:11:20.276 --> 01:11:22.403
You-- You know something's…

1240
01:11:23.362 --> 01:11:24.655
bad. bad. wrong.

1241
01:11:24.738 --> 01:11:26.365
She's hysterical.

1242
01:11:26.448 --> 01:11:30.244
I-- I-- I try to talk to her.
and she can't tell me anything.

1243
01:11:30.327 --> 01:11:31.787
She can't say anything.

1244
01:11:31.870 --> 01:11:33.205
Marcus is like. "What's wrong?"

1245
01:11:33.289 --> 01:11:36.917
And I said. "Just don't go in there.
Do not. Don't go in."

1246
01:11:37.918 --> 01:11:39.169
And. of course.

1247
01:11:39.920 --> 01:11:41.130
I gotta know.

1248
01:11:41.714 --> 01:11:42.548
[gasps softly]

1249
01:11:43.632 --> 01:11:45.801
Marcus opens the door.

1250
01:11:45.884 --> 01:11:50.848
and he backs up.
and I can remember his face.

1251
01:11:50.931 --> 01:11:53.726
And… it's just pure terror.

1252
01:11:56.979 --> 01:11:58.939
And-- And I lost it.

1253
01:12:00.566 --> 01:12:02.943
I-- I started hollering.
I don't know what I said.

1254
01:12:03.027 --> 01:12:04.028
It-- It--

1255
01:12:04.987 --> 01:12:08.115
Worst thing you can imagine.
Worst thing I've ever seen in my life.

1256
01:12:08.198 --> 01:12:09.867
I'm still on the phone with 911.

1257
01:12:09.950 --> 01:12:13.579
and we realized her daughter
was in the house.

1258
01:12:13.662 --> 01:12:14.747
She's three years old.

1259
01:12:14.830 --> 01:12:16.623
[Marcus] So I head back to the door

1260
01:12:16.707 --> 01:12:19.918
and then started calling her name.
screaming it.

1261
01:12:20.002 --> 01:12:23.839
Uh. about the fourth or fifth time.
I heard something.

1262
01:12:24.923 --> 01:12:28.552
and-- and she finally spoke.

1263
01:12:28.635 --> 01:12:30.888
I turned around and looked at Chris.

1264
01:12:30.971 --> 01:12:33.057
I was gonna have to step over her
to get to her.

1265
01:12:33.640 --> 01:12:34.600
Uh…

1266
01:12:35.392 --> 01:12:36.894
And I knew I couldn't do it.

1267
01:12:37.644 --> 01:12:39.688
So I go back in to the kitchen area.

1268
01:12:39.772 --> 01:12:42.399
and I had to step over Reagan

1269
01:12:42.483 --> 01:12:46.362
and-- and walk through the whole… scene.

1270
01:12:46.445 --> 01:12:49.573
And I'm looking in the rooms as I go back.
and I get to the very last bedroom.

1271
01:12:49.656 --> 01:12:54.119
And Reagan's daughter is sitting.
and when I walk into the room.

1272
01:12:54.203 --> 01:12:57.122
she reflexes and draws the covers up.

1273
01:12:57.790 --> 01:13:00.125
And then she notices. recognized me.

1274
01:13:00.209 --> 01:13:05.047
And she jumped up and just ran
and jumped off the bed.

1275
01:13:05.130 --> 01:13:06.215
I had to catch her.

1276
01:13:06.298 --> 01:13:08.759
About that time.
the police officers pulled up.

1277
01:13:08.842 --> 01:13:11.595
I meet the first one.
and I'm like. "Listen. she's pregnant."

1278
01:13:11.678 --> 01:13:12.930
"I don't know…"

1279
01:13:13.013 --> 01:13:15.432
"I don't know if the baby survived or not.
but she's pregnant."

1280
01:13:15.516 --> 01:13:18.936
"I don't know how long this has been.
You know. just please know that."

1281
01:13:21.855 --> 01:13:24.233
[cop 1] We need to know
whether the baby's in there or not.

1282
01:13:25.067 --> 01:13:27.611
'Cause there's an awful lot
of blood everywhere.

1283
01:13:29.279 --> 01:13:32.616
[cop 2] The only way we can
know that is to-- is to roll her over.

1284
01:13:32.699 --> 01:13:33.659
[cop 1] Okay.

1285
01:13:35.744 --> 01:13:37.830
-[cop 3] There's no baby in there.
-[cop 2] No.

1286
01:13:37.913 --> 01:13:39.915
[cop 3] No. There's no baby in there.

1287
01:13:39.998 --> 01:13:42.000
[ethereal music plays]

1288
01:13:42.918 --> 01:13:44.461
[cop 1] So she was pregnant?

1289
01:13:44.545 --> 01:13:46.630
[man] Yes. 36 weeks.

1290
01:13:55.889 --> 01:13:59.143
My brother called me and said.
"Hey. there's some stuff on Facebook

1291
01:13:59.226 --> 01:14:01.895
and it said that the baby
had been taken from her."

1292
01:14:01.979 --> 01:14:07.484
"New Boston Expecting Mother Murdered.
Baby Cut from Womb."

1293
01:14:08.068 --> 01:14:11.572
That's how we found out
that that's what happened to her.

1294
01:14:13.907 --> 01:14:15.242
[click tongue] Anyway…

1295
01:14:17.536 --> 01:14:18.579
[cop 1] She's in there.

1296
01:14:18.662 --> 01:14:21.373
She refuses to have a vaginal check

1297
01:14:21.457 --> 01:14:23.375
to make sure she's not hemorrhaging.

1298
01:14:23.459 --> 01:14:26.086
They've done an ultrasound and HCG.

1299
01:14:26.170 --> 01:14:28.088
and it doesn't show
that she's been pregnant.

1300
01:14:28.172 --> 01:14:29.756
They have the placenta.

1301
01:14:29.840 --> 01:14:31.633
-Where is she?
-[cop 1] She is in the room.

1302
01:14:31.717 --> 01:14:33.260
-You're not letting her leave?
-No.

1303
01:14:33.343 --> 01:14:35.179
-[on phone] Can I help you?
-[cop 1] This is…

1304
01:14:35.262 --> 01:14:36.930
-This is a big deal.
-[cop 1] Yeah.

1305
01:14:37.014 --> 01:14:39.057
[nurse on phone] Okay. yes. Are you ready?

1306
01:14:39.141 --> 01:14:42.728
[cop 1] If there's anything
you need to talk to us about. you can.

1307
01:14:43.770 --> 01:14:47.065
I don't know what everybody
wants me to talk about.

1308
01:14:47.149 --> 01:14:49.067
You gave birth to this child?

1309
01:14:50.277 --> 01:14:51.695
Yes. I--

1310
01:14:52.988 --> 01:14:54.573
[cop 1] We're just making sure.

1311
01:14:54.656 --> 01:14:57.784
{\an8}Did I do something wrong
for them bringing me over here?

1312
01:14:57.868 --> 01:14:59.786
[cop 1] What did you have?
A boy or a girl?

1313
01:14:59.870 --> 01:15:01.872
-A girl.
-[cop 1] A girl. Okay.

1314
01:15:01.955 --> 01:15:03.123
Picked out a name yet?

1315
01:15:03.207 --> 01:15:04.374
Clancy Gaile.

1316
01:15:04.458 --> 01:15:06.043
-Clancy Gaile.
-[cop 1] Clancy Gaile.

1317
01:15:06.919 --> 01:15:08.712
-[doctor] Hi.
-[cop 1] All right.

1318
01:15:09.379 --> 01:15:10.589
Let's see.

1319
01:15:10.672 --> 01:15:11.924
[Chad] So we'll jump out.

1320
01:15:12.508 --> 01:15:13.467
[doctor] Sit you up.

1321
01:15:13.550 --> 01:15:15.594
All right. Well. let me have
them sit you up there

1322
01:15:15.677 --> 01:15:17.387
where I can see what I'm doing.

1323
01:15:21.683 --> 01:15:26.063
So it surely doesn't look
like a baby came out of there.

1324
01:15:27.689 --> 01:15:29.733
I didn't-- It doesn't look
like she had a baby.

1325
01:15:29.816 --> 01:15:30.859
-[cop 1] It doesn't?
-No.

1326
01:15:30.943 --> 01:15:31.860
[cop 1] Okay.

1327
01:15:31.944 --> 01:15:34.821
Does not look
like she had a baby down there.

1328
01:15:34.905 --> 01:15:36.031
[cop 2] Get ready.

1329
01:15:38.242 --> 01:15:39.326
[somber music plays]

1330
01:15:39.409 --> 01:15:40.619
[Taylor sighs]

1331
01:15:42.746 --> 01:15:45.040
Hey. Taylor. So what happened?

1332
01:15:45.958 --> 01:15:47.751
Nothing happened.

1333
01:15:49.711 --> 01:15:51.088
You didn't give birth.

1334
01:15:51.588 --> 01:15:55.467
We're past all this nonsense
about "I wasn't there."

1335
01:15:55.551 --> 01:15:58.512
"I didn't kill nobody."
We're past all of that.

1336
01:15:58.595 --> 01:16:00.806
We know it. We know you did it.

1337
01:16:00.889 --> 01:16:04.601
The bottom line is these cases
are actually pretty simple.

1338
01:16:04.685 --> 01:16:06.311
Murder cases are pretty simple.

1339
01:16:06.395 --> 01:16:09.982
You have a who. what.
when. where. and why.

1340
01:16:13.944 --> 01:16:16.738
[Wade] When I got there.
I asked 'em at the front desk.

1341
01:16:16.822 --> 01:16:19.992
I said. "You know
where I can find Taylor Parker at?"

1342
01:16:21.785 --> 01:16:24.121
And she just kind of looked
at me for a second

1343
01:16:24.204 --> 01:16:26.623
and then paused
and then pointed down the hall.

1344
01:16:26.707 --> 01:16:29.126
and she said.
"Right down here to the right."

1345
01:16:29.209 --> 01:16:32.379
And I walked down there
to the end of the hall and hung a right.

1346
01:16:32.462 --> 01:16:35.757
That's whenever there was
three officers walking towards me.

1347
01:16:35.841 --> 01:16:38.385
come up to me. ask me was I Wade Griffin.

1348
01:16:38.468 --> 01:16:40.846
They said.
"We're gonna restrain you for a little bit

1349
01:16:40.929 --> 01:16:43.724
and take you in
to ask you some questions."

1350
01:16:45.100 --> 01:16:47.853
[Marcus] Somebody says
that there's someone in custody

1351
01:16:47.936 --> 01:16:49.730
in Idabel. Oklahoma.

1352
01:16:51.565 --> 01:16:52.691
[handcuffs clicking]

1353
01:16:54.318 --> 01:16:57.529
One of our friends said.
"Hey. do you know Taylor Parker?"

1354
01:16:57.613 --> 01:17:00.198
And I'm like.
"Homer. do you know Taylor Parker?"

1355
01:17:00.282 --> 01:17:02.826
And he's like. "Yeah.
she was just at our house last night."

1356
01:17:02.909 --> 01:17:05.203
I said. "Well. they're saying
that it's her."

1357
01:17:05.287 --> 01:17:06.538
He's like. "There's no way."

1358
01:17:06.622 --> 01:17:09.833
He said. "She was just at our house
last night. They were talking."

1359
01:17:12.169 --> 01:17:15.464
And I heard Jessica say that she was
the photographer at the wedding.

1360
01:17:18.050 --> 01:17:20.093
{\an8}[Jessica] Sure enough. it was her.

1361
01:17:28.477 --> 01:17:29.436
[cop 1] Watch your toes.

1362
01:17:30.854 --> 01:17:34.441
Under no circumstance
is she to have her phone or purse.

1363
01:17:34.524 --> 01:17:36.151
-[cop 1] Okay. Okay.
-All right?

1364
01:17:36.234 --> 01:17:42.240
She's to be. uh… separated
from her boyfriend who's down there.

1365
01:17:42.824 --> 01:17:44.201
You know the baby's dead?

1366
01:17:44.284 --> 01:17:46.036
-[cop 1] Yeah. I heard.
-Okay.

1367
01:17:48.205 --> 01:17:49.623
-[Chad] Hey. are you Wade?
-Yes. sir.

1368
01:17:49.706 --> 01:17:51.124
Hey. man. I'm sorry you had to wait.

1369
01:17:51.208 --> 01:17:55.671
I've been non-stop phone calls
and everything else.

1370
01:17:56.797 --> 01:17:57.964
Wade. uh…

1371
01:17:59.716 --> 01:18:01.551
Taylor's in jail.

1372
01:18:01.635 --> 01:18:03.428
-In jail?
-Mm-hmm.

1373
01:18:03.512 --> 01:18:05.597
Best we can tell. um…

1374
01:18:06.973 --> 01:18:09.643
looks like she killed a woman
and cut her baby out of her.

1375
01:18:09.726 --> 01:18:12.062
And then passed it off as being hers.

1376
01:18:13.647 --> 01:18:15.691
-Do <i>what?</i>
-Mm-hmm.

1377
01:18:16.942 --> 01:18:17.818
Yep.

1378
01:18:18.402 --> 01:18:19.653
Is the baby alive?

1379
01:18:19.736 --> 01:18:22.656
No. No. it died up here.

1380
01:18:23.281 --> 01:18:26.993
Think they said they got some pulses.
but yeah. it died.

1381
01:18:27.077 --> 01:18:28.370
[melancholic music plays]

1382
01:18:29.621 --> 01:18:32.666
I didn't really have no words
for nothing at that point.

1383
01:18:39.005 --> 01:18:41.466
[sighs heavily]

1384
01:18:43.927 --> 01:18:46.596
Well. I can honestly say
my family was right.

1385
01:18:47.180 --> 01:18:50.308
'Cause they've been calling it
the whole time. and I took up for Taylor.

1386
01:18:50.392 --> 01:18:52.853
Oh. was-- What have they been saying?
That she wasn't pregnant?

1387
01:18:52.936 --> 01:18:54.271
Mm-hmm. Yep.

1388
01:19:03.280 --> 01:19:05.574
[voice breaking] I don't even know
how to explain it.

1389
01:19:06.992 --> 01:19:09.995
Just betrayal from the lies. everything.

1390
01:19:12.289 --> 01:19:16.752
I never. ever wanted anything like that
to ever happen. It was…

1391
01:19:17.377 --> 01:19:19.796
It was unimaginable. what she did.

1392
01:19:22.924 --> 01:19:26.178
I left the police station in Oklahoma
and then come home.

1393
01:19:26.261 --> 01:19:28.972
and there was several state troopers
at the house.

1394
01:19:29.055 --> 01:19:31.558
[trooper] Do we have your consent
to search the property?

1395
01:19:32.350 --> 01:19:33.351
[dog barks]

1396
01:19:33.977 --> 01:19:35.395
[objects clatter]

1397
01:19:46.072 --> 01:19:48.325
[detective] <i>Tell me</i>
<i>about the-- your house.</i>

1398
01:19:49.159 --> 01:19:51.036
<i>You had a nursery set up at the house?</i>

1399
01:19:53.038 --> 01:19:57.375
[Taylor] <i>Yeah. we bought a crib</i>
<i>and clothes and diapers.</i>

1400
01:19:57.459 --> 01:19:58.919
[detective] <i>Who bought all that?</i>

1401
01:20:00.295 --> 01:20:01.838
[Taylor] <i>Me and Wade.</i>

1402
01:20:06.051 --> 01:20:08.553
[detective] <i>Okay. Was he excited</i>
<i>about the baby coming?</i>

1403
01:20:09.513 --> 01:20:10.639
[Taylor] <i>No.</i>

1404
01:20:10.722 --> 01:20:11.848
[detective] <i>Why not?</i>

1405
01:20:13.809 --> 01:20:15.977
[Taylor] <i>He's never been excited about it.</i>

1406
01:20:16.061 --> 01:20:18.647
[sprawling. forlorn music plays]

1407
01:20:21.316 --> 01:20:25.153
[Wade] It was all going through my head
about everything from day one.

1408
01:20:27.948 --> 01:20:28.990
Everything…

1409
01:20:30.283 --> 01:20:31.451
was a lie.

1410
01:20:33.703 --> 01:20:37.207
Very. uh. difficult story to. uh. report.
even read to you tonight.

1411
01:20:37.290 --> 01:20:40.085
{\an8}[reporter 1] <i>A small east Texas community</i>
<i>is grieving the loss</i>

1412
01:20:40.168 --> 01:20:41.461
{\an8}<i>of a New Boston mother.</i>

1413
01:20:41.545 --> 01:20:45.173
I said. "I hope to God…
this is not Taylor."

1414
01:20:45.257 --> 01:20:49.010
[reporter 2] <i>A female suspect was taken</i>
<i>into custody in Oklahoma.</i>

1415
01:20:49.094 --> 01:20:52.764
I just froze. And I said.
"I think I know who that is."

1416
01:20:52.848 --> 01:20:55.934
"That was probably her.
Do you think that was her? Surely not."

1417
01:20:56.017 --> 01:20:59.271
The pit in my stomach just fell
to the bottom as far as it could go.

1418
01:20:59.354 --> 01:21:03.233
It was just… It was just…
A-- My whole insides just sunk.

1419
01:21:03.316 --> 01:21:04.442
Right away.

1420
01:21:04.526 --> 01:21:08.029
Uh. even before the news of who it was.

1421
01:21:08.113 --> 01:21:09.823
we-- we knew who it was.

1422
01:21:09.906 --> 01:21:13.743
Agents say the suspect cut the baby
out of her mother's stomach

1423
01:21:13.827 --> 01:21:16.496
and then tried to claim
the baby as her own.

1424
01:21:16.580 --> 01:21:20.125
{\an8}[reporter 3] <i>27-year-old Taylor Parker</i>
<i>was stopped Friday morning</i>

1425
01:21:20.208 --> 01:21:22.377
{\an8}<i>by Texas troopers in De Kalb.</i>

1426
01:21:22.460 --> 01:21:26.965
{\an8}<i>21-year-old Reagan Hancock</i>
<i>and her unborn child did not survive.</i>

1427
01:21:27.591 --> 01:21:31.720
It was almost impossible
to believe because…

1428
01:21:33.430 --> 01:21:35.056
I had no idea

1429
01:21:35.557 --> 01:21:39.436
someone whom we all had met

1430
01:21:39.519 --> 01:21:44.691
was capable of-- of taking
my sister's life.

1431
01:21:52.699 --> 01:21:59.205
It was very overwhelming
to have to try and process the unknown.

1432
01:21:59.289 --> 01:22:03.877
Father. today again I come to you
lifting the family of this young lady up.

1433
01:22:03.960 --> 01:22:05.170
and this child.

1434
01:22:06.254 --> 01:22:10.926
Father. I pray for Homer above all of 'em.
Father. for Homer's wife. Father.

1435
01:22:11.009 --> 01:22:12.969
When she went to be with you.

1436
01:22:13.053 --> 01:22:15.639
a part of him died this day. Father.

1437
01:22:15.722 --> 01:22:17.432
[Emily] My heart broke

1438
01:22:17.515 --> 01:22:21.311
for… me and my family but also for Homer.

1439
01:22:21.394 --> 01:22:23.396
[melancholic music plays]

1440
01:22:26.775 --> 01:22:30.362
I lost a sister.
but he lost his forever person.

1441
01:22:36.451 --> 01:22:37.911
[inaudible]

1442
01:22:37.994 --> 01:22:40.872
You know. all the questions
you can ask yourself

1443
01:22:41.456 --> 01:22:46.294
when someone is killed is. "Why?"

1444
01:22:49.422 --> 01:22:51.758
[tense music plays]

1445
01:22:58.598 --> 01:23:01.434
{\an8}Everybody around here knew
that she's the one that done it.

1446
01:23:01.518 --> 01:23:03.353
There was no doubt in that.

1447
01:23:03.436 --> 01:23:05.689
In my opinion.
the trial wasn't for guilt or innocence.

1448
01:23:05.772 --> 01:23:07.065
it was for death penalty or not.

1449
01:23:07.148 --> 01:23:11.152
{\an8}Today was all about the lies
prosecutors say Taylor Parker told.

1450
01:23:11.236 --> 01:23:13.571
[reporter 2] <i>Today in court.</i>
<i>Taylor's first husband confirmed</i>

1451
01:23:13.655 --> 01:23:16.574
<i>that she used to practice</i>
<i>other people's handwriting and signatures.</i>

1452
01:23:16.658 --> 01:23:18.952
{\an8}[reporter 1] Today the jurors heard
how Taylor Parker went

1453
01:23:19.035 --> 01:23:21.705
{\an8}to different doctors.
trying to get one to diagnose her

1454
01:23:21.788 --> 01:23:23.915
with the illnesses
she was claiming to have.

1455
01:23:23.999 --> 01:23:26.960
[reporter 2] <i>…argued that Taylor Parker</i>
<i>is a liar and a master manipulator…</i>

1456
01:23:27.043 --> 01:23:29.337
[reporter 1] A real estate agent
said she tried to pull off

1457
01:23:29.421 --> 01:23:31.339
a $20 million real estate deal.

1458
01:23:31.423 --> 01:23:35.135
We didn't know until after the murder

1459
01:23:35.719 --> 01:23:40.473
that all of the people
that we were trying to make contact with

1460
01:23:41.141 --> 01:23:42.183
didn't exist.

1461
01:23:42.267 --> 01:23:45.061
[Rusty] "Shelly Linx with Shell Oil."

1462
01:23:45.145 --> 01:23:47.564
"Blake Lawington. that's my lawyer."

1463
01:23:47.647 --> 01:23:48.857
"Uncle Butch."

1464
01:23:48.940 --> 01:23:54.070
Everybody's just profiled in there
way too conveniently.

1465
01:23:54.154 --> 01:23:56.072
[male voice] <i>Hey. Taylor.</i>
<i>I was giving you a call.</i>

1466
01:23:56.156 --> 01:23:59.492
<i>Got a voicemail from Angela</i>
<i>that said that apparently…</i>

1467
01:23:59.576 --> 01:24:05.081
From multiple phones
to voice-altering apparatus.

1468
01:24:05.165 --> 01:24:06.958
We just couldn't believe
what we were hearing.

1469
01:24:07.042 --> 01:24:11.254
The multiple phones
that she would text herself from.

1470
01:24:11.337 --> 01:24:13.882
the names she would use. the people.

1471
01:24:13.965 --> 01:24:15.717
just all of the lies.

1472
01:24:15.800 --> 01:24:18.303
I still can't understand

1473
01:24:19.137 --> 01:24:21.931
how someone would think
that this was gonna work.

1474
01:24:23.016 --> 01:24:26.436
[reporter] <i>The defense called</i>
<i>Parker's mother Shona Prior to the stand.</i>

1475
01:24:26.519 --> 01:24:28.730
<i>and she testified</i>
<i>for a little over an hour.</i>

1476
01:24:33.651 --> 01:24:35.570
[Lindsey] Everything got revealed.

1477
01:24:35.653 --> 01:24:37.739
Pardon my language. like. "What the fuck?"

1478
01:24:38.281 --> 01:24:41.534
Like. how can one person keep up
with that many lies?

1479
01:24:41.618 --> 01:24:43.870
I would have to carry around
a three-ring binder.

1480
01:24:43.953 --> 01:24:47.540
Everything was a lie.
<i>Everything </i>was a lie.

1481
01:24:50.126 --> 01:24:51.795
[sobs] I remember

1482
01:24:53.129 --> 01:24:56.257
pushing her off me.

1483
01:24:58.093 --> 01:25:01.763
-And she grabbed my hair and hit me.
-[detective sighs]

1484
01:25:01.846 --> 01:25:06.101
And she said.
"You need to wake up. You are lying."

1485
01:25:06.184 --> 01:25:09.854
[reporter] <i>Videos of her police interviews</i>
<i>were shown to the court Wednesday.</i>

1486
01:25:09.938 --> 01:25:12.816
<i>and the investigator who conducted</i>
<i>those interviews testified</i>

1487
01:25:12.899 --> 01:25:15.401
<i>that Parker told wildly different stories.</i>

1488
01:25:15.485 --> 01:25:16.986
-I did not do that!
-[detective] Okay.

1489
01:25:17.070 --> 01:25:18.905
I would admit to something that I did do.

1490
01:25:18.988 --> 01:25:20.615
Okay. Well. I'm just telling you.

1491
01:25:20.698 --> 01:25:23.034
the evidence is there.
it's linked back to you.

1492
01:25:23.118 --> 01:25:24.119
What the fuck?!

1493
01:25:24.202 --> 01:25:26.412
I'm trying to understand
why you did it that day.

1494
01:25:26.496 --> 01:25:29.749
I don't wanna talk about this anymore.
I really don't. [laughs]

1495
01:25:29.833 --> 01:25:31.709
-I understand.
-I don't know. I don't…

1496
01:25:31.793 --> 01:25:34.003
This is-- This is difficult.

1497
01:25:34.087 --> 01:25:36.381
[sobs] I don't want
to talk about this anymore.

1498
01:25:36.464 --> 01:25:40.969
All she did was lay there
and talk to me when I cut her.

1499
01:25:41.052 --> 01:25:42.929
-When you cut her?
-Yes.

1500
01:25:43.012 --> 01:25:44.848
And what did she talk about?

1501
01:25:44.931 --> 01:25:47.559
She just said to take…
She was screaming. "Take her out!"

1502
01:25:47.642 --> 01:25:48.560
What does that mean?

1503
01:25:49.310 --> 01:25:50.728
Take the baby out. Take her out.

1504
01:25:50.812 --> 01:25:53.231
-"Take her out."
-She was screaming at me to take her out.

1505
01:25:53.314 --> 01:25:56.401
-"Her" being the baby.
-She was like. "I'm finished. I'm dying."

1506
01:25:56.484 --> 01:25:58.778
-Okay.
-She was talking to me.

1507
01:25:58.862 --> 01:25:59.696
All right.

1508
01:25:59.779 --> 01:26:03.283
[sobs] But y'all can paint
whatever picture you want.

1509
01:26:03.366 --> 01:26:05.034
You can't tell me this woman said.

1510
01:26:05.118 --> 01:26:09.330
"Take my baby and leave."
and expect me to believe that.

1511
01:26:09.414 --> 01:26:13.543
I was certified as the expert
in OB-GYN for the trial.

1512
01:26:13.626 --> 01:26:18.298
and. uh. even I kind of broke down
on the-- on the stand

1513
01:26:18.381 --> 01:26:20.008
because of how she did it.

1514
01:26:20.592 --> 01:26:24.762
She actually cut behind the uterus
to cut the baby out.

1515
01:26:24.846 --> 01:26:28.850
She flipped the uterus entirely forward
after cutting into the patient's belly.

1516
01:26:31.769 --> 01:26:33.813
It had to be extremely painful.

1517
01:26:33.897 --> 01:26:37.192
I would not know
how anybody could ever do that.

1518
01:26:37.275 --> 01:26:39.485
[detective] You got Wade out of town.

1519
01:26:40.403 --> 01:26:42.739
You made sure Reagan was at home.

1520
01:26:43.573 --> 01:26:47.285
You went to her house
with a diaper bag and a scalpel.

1521
01:26:47.827 --> 01:26:50.205
You got your baby. Wade believed you.

1522
01:26:50.288 --> 01:26:51.915
you proved all these people wrong

1523
01:26:51.998 --> 01:26:55.168
that said you were lying
for the last ten months.

1524
01:26:57.462 --> 01:26:59.297
And you had your "aha" moment…

1525
01:27:01.341 --> 01:27:02.967
at the expense of that.

1526
01:27:03.051 --> 01:27:05.053
[clock ticking]

1527
01:27:10.099 --> 01:27:12.310
Can I please go to the bathroom?

1528
01:27:14.938 --> 01:27:16.064
[gentle music plays]

1529
01:27:16.147 --> 01:27:19.275
[reporter] <i>Convicted killer Taylor Parker</i>
<i>entered the courtroom today</i>

1530
01:27:19.359 --> 01:27:22.487
<i>with her fate in the hands</i>
<i>of a Bowie County jury.</i>

1531
01:27:31.788 --> 01:27:34.916
<i>When court was over.</i>
<i>Parker was sentenced to death row</i>

1532
01:27:34.999 --> 01:27:37.543
<i>for the brutal deaths of Reagan Hancock</i>

1533
01:27:37.627 --> 01:27:40.964
<i>and removing</i>
<i>Hancock's unborn child. Braxlynn.</i>

1534
01:27:41.631 --> 01:27:46.844
<i>The last order given by Judge Tidwell</i>
<i>was "Take her to death row."</i>

1535
01:27:48.554 --> 01:27:51.933
{\an8}A heavy. heavy burden feels lifted.

1536
01:27:52.016 --> 01:27:54.644
{\an8}I feel like now we can start
trying to heal.

1537
01:27:55.228 --> 01:27:58.314
{\an8}[Emily] I'm just… I'm overwhelmed
with happiness it's over.

1538
01:27:58.398 --> 01:28:04.821
{\an8}Because she has been such a burden
in our life for so long now

1539
01:28:04.904 --> 01:28:08.157
{\an8}that I haven't been able
to really think about my sister

1540
01:28:08.241 --> 01:28:10.910
{\an8}without thinking about her.

1541
01:28:10.994 --> 01:28:15.290
{\an8}[reporter] <i>Taylor Parker becomes</i>
<i>the seventh woman on death row in Texas.</i>

1542
01:28:15.373 --> 01:28:17.917
{\an8}<i>Parker is still being processed</i>
<i>at the state prison in Gatesville</i>

1543
01:28:18.001 --> 01:28:20.003
{\an8}<i>before she is sent</i>
<i>to the Mountain View Unit</i>

1544
01:28:20.086 --> 01:28:23.298
<i>to join six other women</i>
<i>awaiting execution.</i>

1545
01:28:27.635 --> 01:28:31.139
[Wade] The whole point behind it all.
I really don't know. but…

1546
01:28:31.764 --> 01:28:34.183
I guess she was hoping
one day I'd finally…

1547
01:28:34.267 --> 01:28:36.769
I'd finally tell her. you know.

1548
01:28:37.645 --> 01:28:40.189
that I loved her.
but I never-- I never did.

1549
01:28:45.028 --> 01:28:48.197
Come on. come on. come on. Come on.

1550
01:28:49.073 --> 01:28:50.283
[continues calling cows]

1551
01:28:50.366 --> 01:28:52.035
[Connie] I watched him cry…

1552
01:28:53.244 --> 01:28:54.537
and cry.

1553
01:28:57.248 --> 01:29:01.252
I love him dearly.
but I really wish he had listened to me.

1554
01:29:03.338 --> 01:29:05.923
People were so angry at what had happened.

1555
01:29:06.007 --> 01:29:07.842
and I didn't blame 'em.

1556
01:29:08.343 --> 01:29:09.552
They avoid him.

1557
01:29:09.635 --> 01:29:13.473
They-- They turn and walk the other way.
and it's hard.

1558
01:29:13.556 --> 01:29:15.350
It's everywhere he goes.

1559
01:29:15.433 --> 01:29:18.561
It never goes away. never will.

1560
01:29:18.644 --> 01:29:20.646
[forlorn music plays]

1561
01:29:21.814 --> 01:29:23.149
[Codey] After all that happened.

1562
01:29:23.232 --> 01:29:26.361
I went over there.
and right when we'd seen each other. we…

1563
01:29:34.494 --> 01:29:37.121
He… [sighs] He said.
"Man. I should have believed you."

1564
01:29:37.205 --> 01:29:39.374
And I said.
"Shit. that's beside the point."

1565
01:29:39.457 --> 01:29:41.626
"We ain't worried about that now."
You know?

1566
01:29:42.502 --> 01:29:46.297
I think everybody that was intimately
involved with that situation feels

1567
01:29:47.173 --> 01:29:49.342
some guilt that will never go away.

1568
01:29:49.842 --> 01:29:53.221
I wouldn't be able to look
at her mother in the face.

1569
01:29:53.304 --> 01:29:55.640
The shame wouldn't let me.
I'd be shameful to do that.

1570
01:29:55.723 --> 01:29:56.933
I couldn't do it.

1571
01:29:57.016 --> 01:30:01.187
[Angela] The people around
that has been involved in this.

1572
01:30:01.270 --> 01:30:04.107
we kind of want to avoid each other.

1573
01:30:05.483 --> 01:30:08.111
Because you don't want
to relive that memory.

1574
01:30:08.736 --> 01:30:10.571
But it's there. and it's…

1575
01:30:11.406 --> 01:30:12.824
It never goes away.

1576
01:30:20.081 --> 01:30:26.003
[Jessica] It is so hard to put into words
what losing a child is like.

1577
01:30:26.921 --> 01:30:29.674
You know. as a mother. that's-- Sh--

1578
01:30:29.757 --> 01:30:33.136
A-- A child is physically
part of you. physically.

1579
01:30:33.219 --> 01:30:37.056
You know. not just emotionally.
not just this little thing you raised.

1580
01:30:37.140 --> 01:30:39.058
They grew inside of you.

1581
01:30:39.142 --> 01:30:43.688
And. um. oh. man. the day she died…

1582
01:30:44.522 --> 01:30:46.732
I've never felt anything like that.

1583
01:30:46.816 --> 01:30:47.817
Um…

1584
01:30:50.236 --> 01:30:52.155
It was-- It--

1585
01:30:52.238 --> 01:30:55.408
Half of me died. Half of me died.

1586
01:30:56.117 --> 01:30:58.035
And. uh. it's not coming back.

1587
01:30:58.703 --> 01:31:02.582
The Jessica that I used to be…
[sobs] …is gone.

1588
01:31:02.665 --> 01:31:06.252
and the part that's left is a part
that I never knew was there.

1589
01:31:06.752 --> 01:31:12.049
You know. when I found her
in the days and weeks after that.

1590
01:31:12.133 --> 01:31:18.639
it was like I had to tell myself.
"Yes. she was real. Yes. she was here."

1591
01:31:18.723 --> 01:31:19.682
You know?

1592
01:31:20.308 --> 01:31:22.477
[voice breaks] It wasn't my imagination.

1593
01:31:22.560 --> 01:31:24.562
[solemn music plays]

1594
01:31:26.355 --> 01:31:27.356
[sniffles]

1595
01:31:38.451 --> 01:31:40.953
[Emily] Me and my husband
got married on… [sniffles]

1596
01:31:41.037 --> 01:31:43.539
…her wedding day. and…

1597
01:31:44.749 --> 01:31:46.918
I was scared to hire a photographer.

1598
01:31:49.545 --> 01:31:52.924
When everything first happened in 2020.

1599
01:31:53.758 --> 01:31:55.468
I prayed she'd go to hell.

1600
01:31:56.427 --> 01:31:57.303
I really did.

1601
01:31:57.386 --> 01:32:00.431
That's what I wanted.
and I was strong believe on that.

1602
01:32:00.515 --> 01:32:03.309
And a preacher told me…

1603
01:32:05.269 --> 01:32:06.979
"Everyone can be forgiven."

1604
01:32:08.439 --> 01:32:10.233
"Just not by us."

1605
01:32:10.900 --> 01:32:14.445
Her just answering to God
is all I'm asking at this point.

1606
01:32:15.446 --> 01:32:19.408
If she does ask God for forgiveness.

1607
01:32:19.492 --> 01:32:21.452
I pray that she means it.

1608
01:32:23.955 --> 01:32:28.000
Because… for a demon like her.

1609
01:32:29.210 --> 01:32:30.836
a demon like Taylor.

1610
01:32:32.255 --> 01:32:33.923
hell would be easy.

1611
01:32:36.551 --> 01:32:37.969
[solemn music continues]

1612
01:34:09.435 --> 01:34:10.603
[music ends]

1613
